text:
#thisisnotconsent (これは同意じゃない)

アイルランドで17歳の少女がレイプされた事件。
しかし被告の判決は無罪。
事件当時、被害者の少女が着用していたのはレースのtバック。
このことから性行為は同意だったと、加害者側の弁護士が主張。
陪審員が全員一致で被告を無罪とした。

世界中で#thisisnotconsent と抗議が殺到している。

text:
find somebody that walks beside you.
.
.
not in front. not behind. but beside you.
.
.
a partnership.
.
.
someone who supports you, but also pushes you.
.
.
someone who dreams with you, but let's you dream for yourself.
.
.
someone who says i love you every day, & tells you you're beautiful regardless of how you look.
.
.
someone who listens to you & is willing to meet you halfway. who makes you laugh & puts up with your crazy antics. .
.
someone who says how we can make things better because i'm never giving up on you, on us, or on our family.
.
.
that's what you should have in a healthy relationship. there will be ups and downs, fights & makeups. but you feel safe & know they will always fight to make things better.
.
.
it may have taken me to go through some hard times.. but i would gladly do it again if it led me to one of the best people i know.👫💏 #thisiswhatahealthyrelationshiplookslike

text:
positive mindset doesn’t fix trauma.
so often we hear the simple, yet sometimes confronting phrase, ‘it’s all about a positive mindset.’
yes, i agree, to an extent.
and this is where we begin.
someone who has experienced great trauma will not and cannot simply wish away the feelings of immeasurable panic, or inconsolable sadness. it’s not simply a matter of cheering up or willing yourself to be happy.

full article on my website: www.violetambagia.com

#survivor #metoo #fighters

text:
"whenever a patriarchy wants females to populate a new territory or replenish an old one, big breast and hips become admirable", citing the marilyn monroe type figures that became popular in post war western societies. "as soon as increased populations wasn't desirable or necessary, hips and breasts were de-emphasised. think twiggy look that arrived in n the 1960s.
but whether bosomy or flat, zaftig or thin, the female ideal remains weak, and it stays that way unless women ourselves organise to change it... the point is: only when women rebel against the patriarchal standards does female muscle become more accepted" - gloria steinem @gloriasteinem 
when i read this, i had to write it down. it makes so much sense and really made me think. .
.
.

but whether bosomy or flat, zaftig or thin, the female ideal remains weak, and it stays that way unless women ourselves organise to change it... the point is: only when women rebel against the patriarchal standards does female muscle become more accepted" - gloria steinem @gloriasteinem 
when i read this, i had to write it down. it makes so much sense and really made me think. .
.
.

text:
dear fuckboys
no, not the dumb ones
who wear machismo like cologne
and walk with honey singh rapping in the background
the smart fuckboy
the intelligence fuckboy
the apparently woke fuckboy
this one's for you

we are all sunflowers
not even trying to be rose
learning to accept our bodies
slowly sinking in our own skin
learning to carry the baggage
of our insecurities
and when we look at you
we don't see if your jaws are chiseled
or if your eyes are dreamy
we see you for the thoughts that you share

you send us feminist, pro-pride posts
and science memes
you flood our texts with potter trivia
and talk at lengths about books
and politics
and nolan movies
we get smitten
we feel like the ladies of an austen novel
being wooed by the gentleman on a high horse

and then you ask about my dreams
my passions
my fears
i lose my heart to you
and let you have me
when my skin touches yours
and my soul latches on to you
you claim your conquest
and you walk away

you are like a swiggy order with a zomato label
you are the same dumb fuckboy, but with some preparation
you present intelligence instead of dick pics
and parcel your exploitation as commitment phobic
you don't just take our body
you take a part of our heart
and make us blame ourselves for your leaving
because a woke guy never kisses and tells right?

so, you, my dear
have been hunting for so long now
have been calculating probabities of who would sleep
for how much of wokeness
and who would keep calm after your mess
and see you as an unattainable piece of treasure
while you count us just as a statistic
i see you
and i know you
you might walk with beethoven as background music
but i ain't deaf.

p.s. please note that in this poem i talked about consensual sex with a bad person who would leave you after that. this doesn't count as #metoo.
p.p.s. no offense meant to swiggy or zomato.
also, people who know me, don't go around tying this poem up to my personal life. poetry sometimes is written based on observation too.

text:
the 7th oil that comes in your starter kit is raven! raven is a blend of ravintsara (key ingredient in vick’s but the real deal!), peppermint, lemon, wintergreen, and eucalyptus radiata. it is amazing for respiratory support, especially around this time of year! 
i love to put a drop of raven in the corner of the shower when i’m sniffly. it along with the steam helps to open everything up! you can  use a drop with some coconut oil and rub it on to your chest as well! 
breathe easy by diffusing raven, it is great with lemon! do not diffuse raven around those who are under 6, instead use snifflease from the kid’s line, it is already pre-diluted and safe to use with littles! 
what is your fave way to use raven? .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: i feel broken. i am aware that to be human is to be broken; however, awareness all too often fails to be a source of catharsis. moreover, this is a platitude i preach regularly, but to feel it so viscerally in the moment reminds me that words more often lose the sheer weight of the context of reality. the culmination of past traumas and contemporary injuries, as well as illness, has thrown a reckoning upon me. i’ve been breaking down; i know that’s okay. after i was raped 3 years ago, i felt castrated. i searched for this facade of manhood that could fill this void that was taken from me. at the time, i couldn’t find strength in my broken state. as time unfolded before me, i found strength not in masculinity but in the wisdom i found in the very events that broke me. now, many project the perception of strength upon me. i feel obligated to live up to this, because i too project this notion upon me. it is a pillar of stability i rely on to make it from day to day, but i have to be reminded where i originally found this strength. where i often go wrong is failing to remember that strength and vulnerability aren’t mutually exclusive; there is strength that can be derived from the shattered pieces of our existence. this is where we grow stronger. often, i operate subconsciously on this philosophy, but the world needs to knock me off my bike from time to time. i feel broken in this moment, and that’s okay. life goes on. strength will be unearthed in this time; i will cary on a little stronger, a little wiser, and more broken than i was before. remember, be vulnerable; we all are.

text:
what survivors are really asking for when they want to be believed:
it’s important to remember, believing a survivor does not begin and end with simply believing that they have been raped.

believing them must extend to believing their symptoms, believing their experience, believing that they are trying their best, even when you can’t understand how this bright, previously successful person’s new ‘best’ could possibly be as basic as leaving the house that day.

this idea that strength means remaining unaffected is pervasive, but ridiculous. strength is fully acknowledging how horrible your experience was, and choosing to live, anyway. just because i’m here and speaking out today doesn’t mean i’m okay. i was shocked to lose so much of what i had once thought was unchangeable about myself. everything changed, and i would have begun to heal so much sooner had i not tried so hard to force myself into being fine. i was not fine, and i had the right to be broken, because someone tried to break me.
.
.
.

text: 2018 has brought so much progress for nevertheless - we’ve traveled coast to coast, done over 40 interviews exploring the topic of sexual harassment from every angle. i’ve been challenged, enlightened, discouraged, uplifted, and perhaps gone through every emotion this year as it happens to have existed alongside my transition in to motherhood. and every shoot i have been so grateful for the openness and vulnerability of each person we have been lucky enough to make contact with. their stories are my stories, and it is my responsibility now to share them with the world. ✨ biggest shout out to my wonderful friend and collaborator alana finkelstein (ok ok, her name is alana fickes) for her beautiful cinematography and her willingness to always jump in with her heart wide open ♥️ and my friend carla romo for being the best research producer a gal could ask for! so much more to come - we move in to post-production now with likely a few more shoots next year to finish up. onward!  #nevertheless #metoo #timesup

text:
on day 3, after the centenary of the armistice darkest hour...
let's move on to the winners.. and who better symbolizes victory for great britain than winston churchill.. the darkest hour... winston churchill... hero to most of the world.. villian to most indians....!
the movie is about churchill's accent to prime ministerial position... and the first tense month where united kingdom nearly became an subject of hitler and his nazi... mostly  the story  is truly depicted. as usual, in biopics, the director has used his poetic license. specially in depicting the scenes of the war cabinet. the sets are superb, showing the majesty of the uk, but also the dark mood in those tough times. clementine, his wife, is probably the only one who loved churchill and she is well played by kristen scott thomas. very realistic and the domestic tensions are well depicted. the hero worship by ms layton, starting from fear to complete hero worship is a transition which is classic.. the dialogues are in a typical style of churchill... little mumbling but great oratory skill.

the best  in the movie is gary oldman and his make up and his old man act and his shuffling... the scene where he comes out of the bathroom, stark naked, while dictating to ms layton, in todays #metoo situation would have ensured his resignation (and the whole course of history may have changed)

the british history lessons, along with 'dunkirk', 'the kings speech' and 'the crown' are now complete!

overall, a dark and wordy movie, must watch for history lovers

3.5/5 for me
ps
on a side note, if there's one historical character i hate with all my heart, it's churchill, who managed to create two famines in india killing a million people and forced by his delayed actions the partition of india....

text: on sunday, a&e premiered #theclintonaffair — the first of a six-part series that details bill clinton’s affair with then 22-year-old white house intern monica lewinsky and coincides with the 20th anniversary of his impeachment. many have argued, in the age of #metoo, that mr. clinton owes ms. lewinsky an apology; many also view ms. lewinsky — once dismissed as “ditsy,” predatory,” and “a little tart” in newspapers such as this one — as a powerful spokeswoman for this era, highlighting all sorts of critical nuances about power, consent and public shame. gender editor @jessicabennett profiled ms. lewinsky three years ago as she prepared to speak out publicly for the first time. she spoke bluntly about her regrets about relationship with the president — but also about the searing impact of its the aftermath. “anybody who has gone through any kind of trauma knows it doesn’t just go away with a snap of the fingers,” ms. lewinsky said. “it lives as an echo in your life. but over time the echo becomes softer and softer.” re-read that profile at the link in bio, or check out the new series on @aetv. 📷: @damonwinter

text:
yet another incident blinded by caste in this era. i was surprised it is not common only in india but elsewhere in the world too. are we so bonded with caste that it pushes us to man slaughter forgetting that we are blessed with 6 senses ? it isn't honour killing blinded by rage. it's a murder that is planned. a 14 year old beheaded for her #metoo in name of caste , a young couple thrown into the river by the relations and a husband murdered in front of his pregnant wife. there are many such acts of arrogance that never see the daylight. nothing is more brutal when the society is the silent spectator. there are voices here and there but not enough to shake and uproot the cause. the first thing we teach our kids is "jathigal ilayadi papa - there is no caste my dear" , but we need a caste certificate for admissions. irony.

text:
first off, thank you to all the folks who write their own comments and have taken the time to make genuine connections. y'all are why social media started to become a thing in the first place, please don't ever change that. i just need break from daily writing posts so that i can allocate more of my writing time to slams, paid projects, and longer works. i'm also just tired of seeing so many poets buy in to the basic structures and over-used themes because that's the vast majority of what they see on this site. i'll be shifting this account down to about two poems a week along with more visual art as well as some slam excerpts in stories. 
edit: wanted to explain the metaphor in lines 7 and 8 because there's a highly publicized case in the news right now that's a prime example of it.  some people have compared the sweep of people opening up about their #metoo experiences to "the boy who cried wolf" because they think both the story and the movement are about seeking attention and causing a ruckus. it's also been talked about because in the rare circumstance people falsely report such crimes society uses it as an excuse to not take action to end rape culture. the real moral of that story is even if a liar is telling the truth people assume otherwise. and we survivors are far too often assumed to be lying until proven otherwise. asking "what were you wearing?" is one example of this. we are asssumed to be asking for it, therefore people assume consent.

text: it’s official: 2018 is toxic☠️. toxic’ is oxford’s word of the year. surprised🤷‍♀️? @nytimes published an article stating that oxford’s 2018 word of the year is toxic for a variety of reasons. the article stated, “katherine connor martin, the company’s head of u.s. dictionaries, said there had been a marked uptick of interest in the word on its website over the past year. but the word was chosen less for statistical reasons, she said, than for the sheer variety of contexts in which it has proliferated, from conversations about environmental poisons to laments about today’s poisonous political discourse to the #metoo movement, with its calling out of “toxic masculinity. in fact, martin said, the committee initially considered choosing “toxic masculinity,” until it realized how widespread “toxic” itself had become...” i know that’s what i’ve been taking about all year🙀. #switchtosafer #bethechange #inittogether #cancer #cleanbeauty #cleanliving #momlife #momofboys #toxic #beautycounter

text:
part 2 - meeting andy 
cont. .

andy told me there’s still 2 billion souls that still need to come over ( not sure what that meant) maybe there will be a shift at some point in order for their souls progression. .

he said that he saw i was getting ready to explode in a massive way and that this part of my journey,  i would have to go at it alone.  i understood what he meant and it felt very on point. .

he said many other things which i promptly forgot even though i tried writing as fast as i could when i woke up. 
we really had a long wonderful conversation , he was very nice and i felt like mike was in great hands with his new friend. .

in my minds eye i could see mike coming in and out of our conversation, just like he would if he were alive.  he started talking baseball made a comment about "blue,...something". andy knew he was talking about the dodgers, as if they had many of these conversations. 
it was the longest dream i had with mike.  he looked like his amazing self.  doing what he did over here. making friends, connecting with everyone.  andy was a very kind and sincere man, who seems to take life more seriously than mike, which is great for mike to have on the other side.  someone to ground him without judgement.

and i feel like mike is keeping andy busier than he would have expected, doing all sorts of things outside his comfort zone.
.

i don't think this would surprise anyone that knew mike.  on the next slide ➡️➡️ you’ll see my husband in the same shirt and glasses he wore in my dream.  you can catch the longer version my following me on fb https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=1623319080

text: censorship is all around us, from social media to television to academia to government institutions. what is hidden and blocked from view reveals the cultural norms that override expression and - subsequently - artists' efforts to contest such norms. alison stinely's art was censored before finding a place at the linda matney art gallery. women artists, like stinely, have had their ideas blocked by institutions for centuries. how does her experience with censorship fit within the era of the #metoo movement? what does the silencing of female expression in today's culture mean for women? join alison stinely, diana blanchard gross, vittorio colaizzi, lita tirak and john lee matney held a rigorous panel discussion at the linda matney art gallery on saturday, may 19th at 2pm "...[stinely] and her proxies refuse to be labeled, restricted, or contained and possess an otherworldly strength beyond the surface of shiny broken fragments." -dr. margaret richardson. director@lindamatneygallery.com  #williamsburgva  tnewportnewsva #norfolkva #odu #artcollection  #757art #richmondva #erie  #malenude #figurativepainting #maleandfemale #3dprinting #florence  #mixedmedia #rva #artmuseum #acrylicpainting #investmentart #censored #sculpture #gilded #popsurrealism #oilpainting #femaleartist #paintings #artist #narrativeart

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
part of #healing and moving through feelings of #guilt and #shame is finding allies, people who #inspire and remind you of your #beauty and divine #nature. healing is the heart of the many global movements for #reparations and #decolonization. and it is what i’m finding in #isabela, borikén aka #puertorico, which is the world’s oldest colony. 
the #nativepeople of borikén are #taíno. the earliest colonizers were #spanish and mostly jews who, in 1492, were expelled from #spain. many were #conversos, jews who hid their religion to survive. #trauma, however, always erupts. and it did on the shores of the #caribe when #fuckcolumbus arrived: the people who greeted the sailors were roasted alive. colonialism is #religious violence like the #inquisition. 
healing is the polar opposite of what most of the world's political and business leadership seek to sell. hence this pithy hashtag, which speaks to my own sorry experiences over the last four years.

#googleprotectssexualpredators.

if you know me and my work, you know that i write a lot about guilt and shame as currencies. i also talk about using them to fund healing projects such as a migrating university and decolonial business academy. it’s true.

while i’d rather not shame and guilt people and companies into giving monies, we need the cash. i do. just read “$6.42 and the dream” on linkedin. believe me, i don't want to remember the how and why of how google has been protecting one sexual predator that i know by name and many others such as andy rubin, but sometimes we can't forget or move forward without a formal reckoning and financial reparations.

that's what #metoo and #timesup and #niunamenos and #balancetonporc represent: reckoning and reparations.

sometimes we experience situations where healing can most fully happen when financial and material resources are available. decolonization and reparations are not metaphors. they are economic relationships that promote love, healing, and resilience. that's why i see guilt and shame as global currencies. may they soon go out of fashion, just like #fastfashion.

text:
sorteo 15 paquetes libro-tarot de la diosa triple. 📕"por qué el amor nos duele tanto" ha llegado a su cuarta edición. el libro se escribió antes del #metoo y en aquel momento publicar una novela sobre acoso, maltrato y abuso sexual parecía veneno comercial. contra todo pronóstico, sin una sola reseña en medios ni campaña de publicidad, ha llegado a la cuarta edición.

por eso, he decidido invocar la protección de la diosa triple para que me dé suerte, porque la protección de la industria editorial y los medios no la tengo. .

para conseguir el libro-tarot: hazte una foto con el libro "por qué el amor nos duele tanto" ( en versión digital o papel, da igual), o bien con un cartel que diga por qué el amor nos duele tanto y cuélgala con el siguiente pie de foto: 
#porqueelamornosdueletanto de @lucia_etxebarria_  ha llegado a su cuarta edición. más información en el perfil de la autora. 
los paquete libro-tarot son los últimos de una edición limitada y no los puedes comprar 
sí que puedes comprar "por qué el amor nos duele tanto" en  fnac, corte inglés o casa del libro. o, si lo quieres firmado y dedicado por navidad, puedes escribir a comproeselibroya@gmail.com y te lo envío yo con estas manitas.

pero date prisa si escribes porque la remesa para libros dedicados es limitada. 
#feminismo #psicología #literatura #resiliencia
#eresloquesuperas

text_retweet:
walaupun ruang lingkup dalam seminar ini adalah “dunia kerja” namun bagi kami mengundang kawan-kawan muda kampus merupakan sebuah kebutuhan. berbagi pengalaman tentang strategi untuk menuntut dan menciptakan ruang aman bebas dari kekerasan dalam dunia kerja, saat ini menjadi penting di tengah situasi kampus yang juga rentan kekerasan seksual. ruang akademik pun sebenarnya tidak terlepas dari konsep dunia kerja yang akan menjadi bagian dalam seminar tersebut di atas.

repost @mahardhikakita with @get_repost
・・・
babak baru perlawanan terhadap kekerasan seksual telah datang. suara korban tak bisa lagi disangkal. mendesak peradilan yang berpihak dan menuntut setiap tempat jadi ruang aman dan menghargai perempua. .
.
namun begitu sikap para pengambil kebijakan belum sesuai harapan. korban balik disudutkan, diminta untuk mengurangi kebebasan, dan malah diancam pidana dan dikriminalisasikan. .
.
teman-teman semua, ayo datang dan ramaikan seminar sehari #akhirisekarang kekerasan seksual dan diskriminasi gender dalam dunia kerja. bersama dengan beragam organisasi serikat buruh, mari suarakan dan kuatkan perlawanan kita, mewujudkan pabrik, kantor, kampus, lingkuan kita aman dan bebas kekerasan seksual. .
.
selasa, 27 november 2018, pukul 09.00 s.d 17.30 di gedung lbh jakarta
.
.
konfirmasi : nje 0859-4532-8794 / https://docs.google.com/forms/d/19fhxy6148nnbezbthvi11zdrlg0dl8prpwtrfceobsy/edit (link on bio)

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
time’s flying ⏱ (as well as my money does 😜💸). so once again, a new week is on the horizon. i still relax in #bali and enjoy my last week in #uluwatu. btw, yes, i am a female solo traveler and #notlost at all. 💪🏼😃 traveling alone is not always easy, but it’s much more intense than traveling as a couple. although it’s unfortunately more demanding being a girl 💁🏼‍♀️ than it is for guys 💁🏽‍♂️, because lots of peeps think you’re just looking for a man. wait a minute. no, i am not. 🤦🏼‍♀️
nevertheless, there’s one thing i learned during the last years, which anyone should keep in mind: self-love is not selfish.☝🏼you cannot truly love another person until you know how to love yourself. ☺️ so equally whether you are male or female, never forget to take care of loving yourself to live a blessed, balanced and fulfilled life. 💚🙏🏼
—

text:
good morning my wonderful people. 
omg we are super excited because 🥁🥁🥁🥁🥁🥁🥁it’s one week to our anniversary celebration god has been good to us and we are super happy for helping us thus far. how are you doing and hope you enjoyed your weekend. i pray this new week god will surprise you real good.
this week on @lifematterswithaanuadedire it is an honour bringing back our very first guest on the show. my amazing guest @christianah_akindolie, she is a writer, author, child protection advocate, family safety advocate. she is the founder and executive director of christianah fate foundation, a non-governmental organization based in nigeria, tasked with a vision to see children enjoy their childhood without form of abuse.
she is one of pioneering child protection and family safety advocate in nigeria with a passion to ensure children and women are protected from abuse.  she also trained as a child protection advocate at the kidpower child protection advocates institute, california – usa, using and teaching safety skills from kidpower program. she is a certified neuro linguistic programming practitioner and an emotional intelligence specialist. she has also obtained living works, canada certificate (asist) to help individuals having suicidal thoughts.
she will be discussing 
protecting your children from the prey
- at home - in school - religious organizations
- having them to open up
you sure wont want to miss this great discuss and please send in your questions to us via dm or email.
you dont wanna miss this episode.
 dont forget to tune in. details on flier. don't forget to tune in this week and tell a friend.
.
.

text:
剛從內地工作回港，不得不對呂麗瑤性侵案，呢單我之前寫過的案件，就判決再講下睇法： 「惟裁判官亦指，事主勇敢及無私的行為，會令社會變得越來越公平；無論裁決是否如事主所願，她無懼社會大眾的壓力，挺身公開事件，是極為值得讚揚的行為。」 林作：裁判官素質一直為大律師界有能之輩所詬病。這番說話完全邏輯上是矛盾的 - 公開事件值得讚揚，那麼代表受害人所說的事件本身就是真的 - 那麼為何不判被告入罪？！裁判官難道是說他信事主但無法入被告罪？！裁判官有權這麼說嗎？！ 「主任裁判官練錦鴻裁決指，事件在案發後8年才曝光，全因事主受到外國運動員「#metoo」運動啟發，而她本身頗有知名度，令案件受廣泛關注。練官又指，不相信事主公開事件的動機是因為報復心理或個人利益。」 林作：裁判官，和很多法官的問題，是自己背景的離地。他們可能最不懂的，就是娛樂、或和曝光有關的行業。對不起，但他完全沒有資格說公開事件沒有個人利益動機。總的來說，我真的很少看到有裁判官判案講話講到如此出格的。難道他想沾下光，順便做 #metoo kol 嗎？

事實是，被告教練被判無罪。請大眾同裁判官本人都尊重裁決。公道自在人心，但裁判官這麼說話，似乎會令人對法治感到失望。這是我覺得最可悲的。

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

.

.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
[男女複数で構成されてるグループをテラスハウスと言うの、やめます]

先日、人生で初めて男女複数でディズニーに行きました。そこへはチャリで行ける距離に住んでいる自分ですがコスト面からあまり行くことは少なく行っても男子だけで行くことが多かったからです。さてタイトルの説明ですが、自分は中学三年生の頃極度の女性嫌いを煩わせ、以降男女複数で仲良くしてるグループを、僕の最も嫌いな番組、テラスハウスに被せてそう呼んでいました。どうして男女複数が嫌いかというと、自分以外の同姓が明らかに他の異性を意識したふるまいをするのを見るのが本当に気持ち悪いと思ってしまうからです。高校の時は常に男子のみのグループで遊んでました。そのスタンスはきっと大学でも変わらないのだろうと思っていましたが、
留学先で出会ったこのメンバーはそんな僕の考えを砕いてくれる、大切なお仲間となっていてくれます。bias major, eugenics minor の僕ですが、最近は様々な点において変わっているような気がしますね。さて、誰かのインスタを覗けば必ず存在するディズニーの投稿ですが、写真にバリエーションは無いため差をつけるには俊足を履くかキャプションにこだわるしかありません。ですが基本人は差をつけるためにインスタをやっていないので、投稿はほとんど以下の３つに分類することができます。

①where dreams come true:) 定番ですねー。僕の夢は鳥になること[icuhs2018卒アル参照]なのでこれは却下ですね、叶ってないので。

➁このメンバー楽しすぎ😂🤚また行くしかない😜#内輪にしか伝わらないそのグループで出来た造語#内輪にしか伝わらないそのグループで出来た造語2#変なグループ名  これはよくありますね、snsにおける内輪投稿はよく血みどろの議論に発展いたしますが僕的にはいいんじゃないかと思います。誰かのためにやるsnsなんてごめんですよねー、ただ内輪ネタは生理的嫌悪があるので却下です、あとこういうタイプの投稿する男は飲みの席で女とのワンチャンしか狙ってないし一日携帯いじってるしスマホケースが女ウケの良さそうなキャラだし、リズムネタの芸人に大爆笑する

③今日は〇〇メンでディズニー✨トイマニのファストパス取ってタワテラ乗ってからレイジングスピリッツ2時間待ち笑その後はシーライダー乗って号泣😂陸に上がりたくなくなってしまった。そうは言えど我は慶應、陸の王者慶應。いつまでも夢を引きずることなどなく、その日限りの儚い願いと考慮し合計１２回搭乗。

よくあるその日に乗ったアトラクションの説明ですが、これ誰が聞きたいですか？？ [まとめ]
ディズニーの投稿はこの３つ以外ありません。全インスタのディズニーの投稿を確認しましたがこれに分類することができました。この３つに変わる、見る人が笑顔になれるキャプションを思いついたら、教えてください。ディズニーの投稿が増えがちなこの時期、是非今一度自分のディズニーの投稿を振り返ってみてはいかがでしょうか？ではまた。
[参照]
williams, timothy w. exploring japanese women's work experiences in tokyo, japan: a phenomenological study, university of phoenix, ann arbor, 2010. proquest, https://search.proquest.com/docview/874660910?accountid=10105.

sandra e garhttps the women who created #metoo long before hashtags the new york times, 2017
https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/20/us/me-too-movement-tarana-burke.html

munchus, george i.,ii. "discrimination against working women in japan." women in management review,  vol. 8, no. 1, 1993, pp. 9. proquest, https://search.proquest.com/docview/213149939?accountid=10105. 
mizuho aoki house husbands gaining acceptance in japan as gender stereotypes ease the japan times 2016  https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2016/04/28/national/social-issues/house-husbands-gaining-acceptance-japan-gender-stereotypes-ease/#.w-j3ozp7sk8

先日、人生で初めて男女複数でディズニーに行きました。そこへはチャリで行ける距離に住んでいる自分ですがコスト面からあまり行くことは少なく行っても男子だけで行くことが多かったからです。さてタイトルの説明ですが、自分は中学三年生の頃極度の女性嫌いを煩わせ、以降男女複数で仲良くしてるグループを、僕の最も嫌いな番組、テラスハウスに被せてそう呼んでいました。どうして男女複数が嫌いかというと、自分以外の同姓が明らかに他の異性を意識したふるまいをするのを見るのが本当に気持ち悪いと思ってしまうからです。高校の時は常に男子のみのグループで遊んでました。そのスタンスはきっと大学でも変わらないのだろうと思っていましたが、

today's challenge: tell us how i play and what needs to transform asap to change the relationship interactions in my life?
* who do i play ping pong with? ** think about the people from challenge day 5
* what does my body language look lwhen you play ping pong?
* how does your voice tone change during the game?
* what are the areas of conflict involved in the game?
* do any of these ping pong games mirror childhood experiences that you observed or engaged in?

day 6. damn i am avoiding this question all day once again, yet the question is not going anywhere.  yet it honestly . . . that is answering this question.  i play ping pong 🏓 with 👉🏼myself👈🏼 back and forth all f*€n day long!  baha!! i have to laugh bc it is silly!😆 yet, if i do not catch myself i will feed my source emotion of rage and drive myself into an emotional addiction cycle of grief and then anxiety like we talked about on day 3.👊🏼
.
my body language.  rage, is “black outs” and “check outs.” this then causes me to become grief stricken and hayl sometimes it is a supreme victory for me to have a shower.🛁🚿
.
areas of conflict.  i will replay scenarios in my head where i am thinking “people should not do this to me” {feed myself the rage} instead of simply taking myself out of the situation in the first place.
.
voice tone.  i become very quiet or downright silent during my rage.  sometimes i do if i can find my logical words.  i seldom give it out anymore.  perhaps this is why i cycle into grief and then anxiety.
.
childhood experiences.  yes most assuredly.  it took me a minute to figure this one out.  now i know why.  rage causes me to black out.  now, i “eat my words,” which then causes me to go into grief.  i was not allowed to be angry as a child.  it is a “sin” or “bad.” if i am blacking out i am having trouble remembering.  yet what child does not get angry?  and who says it is not okay to be angry?  i most assuredly am paying the price today yet i am grateful that i have tools to get me out of this muck! ⚒🧰 .

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

emarchele24
"samedi 24 novembre, soyons des milliers à marcher pour en finir avec les violences sexistes et sexuelles et pour dire stop aux violences faites aux femmes ! [ 📢  📢 ] notre appel !

nous sommes des millions de femmes et d’enfants à avoir subi et à subir encore des violences sexistes et sexuelles qui nous pourrissent la vie.

nous sommes des millions à avoir vu ces violences abîmer nos amies, nos sœurs, nos amoureuses, nos mères, nos enfants ou nos collègues.

dans l’espace public, au travail, à la maison, nous exigeons de vivre en libeé, sans injures, ni menaces, sans sifflements ni harcèlement, sans persécution ni agressions, sans viols, sans blessures, sans exploitation de nos corps, sans mutilations, sans meures.

aucune d’entre nous ne doit souffrir de violences et d’attaque à l’intégrité corporelle parce qu’elle est femme. aucune d’entre nous ne doit cumuler les violences car elle cumule les discriminations. nous exigeons que les enfants soient protégés de ces violences.

l’impunité des agresseurs doit cesser. la solidarité avec les victimes doit être renforcée. des mesures ambitieuses doivent être prises, des moyens dégagés pour que ça change vraiment.

nous allons marcher pour montrer notre nombre, notre force et notre détermination contre ce système inégalitaire et violent. ► après  ensemble  pour gagner !

depuis des années, les femmes se lèvent pour dire stop. aujourd’hui, nous invitons toutes celles et ceux qui veulent comme nous mettre fin aux violences sexistes et sexuelles à marcher avec nous." ▬▬▬▬▬▬
rdv le 24 novembre, 14h30, à marseille !

text:
idag på internationella mansdagen vill jag passa på att hylla alla starka, fantastiska män! alla ni som vågar ta det där snacket med polarna om att samhället kanske inte alltid är så schysst mot kvinnor. som vågar stötta och backa upp när vi behöver det som mest. som ställer sig bredvid en kvinna när hon vågar ifrågasätta och kritisera förutsättningarna. er vill jag hylla idag! tack för att ni finns, ni är viktigare än någonsin! ⭐️
till alla gubbslem som tycker att vi ska veta vår plats, som tycker att #metoo gick för långt och som är livrädda för att dela med sig av alla privilegier som kommer gratis bara för att man har en snopp vill jag vänligt men bestämt säga; dra åt pipsvängen. nu.

text:
just for being women.
just for who we are,
which we could not control:
that luck or chance
that changed our lives.

text:
so happy to have been nominated for the ‘future classic women awards’ and to be singing at the nominees concert on friday.
come and join us.

come along to meet some of our amazing nominees in a live snippet of the radio programme "future classic women awards". artists lined up for the event include - lucy kay (finalist of britain’s got talent and no.1 classical charts)
- the ayoub sisters (nominees at classic brits awards and classic fm artists), - matilda lloyd (brass winner of bbc young musician of the year),
- belle chen (amazing composer/experimental/pianist),
- francesca matta (the most delicious italian soprano in london (listen to her podcast to know more)
- bryony james (extra talented cellist from the #pavaoquartett)
- april fredrick (mesmerising cutting edge soprano)
- cordelia williams charlton (piano winner of bbc young musician of the year)
- clara schumann (aka elena mazzon with her clara: a show for an actress and a piano)

presenter and guest performer: stefania passamonte

catch up on their intriguing interviews, full of music, crazy stories, funny mishaps and challenging experiences (from the #metoo movement to the #bigc of inspiring cancer survivors) : live very day at 10am and 10pm on the multi-awards non-profit women’s radio station https://stream.radio.co/sf9c0cf965/listen
or on the “future classic women awards” podcast: http://womensradiostation.com/shows/future-classic-women-awards/

tickets trough eventbrite:
£10 adults
£5 concession

text:
¡muy buenos días!

estas imágenes son de dos de los talleres realizados con grupos de primaria, en los cuales el alumnado ha compartido experiencias personales de violencia de género, que creemos que es esencial que os paréis a escuchar... para eso, os invitamos a las jornadas "ande yo valiente... #metoo getafense", en la cual escucharemos las portavocías de alumnas y alumnos de primaria y secundaria que dan voz a las vivencias de sus compañeros y compañeras de grupo.

escucharemos representantes de 8 grupos y 4 centros centros públicos de getafe: ceip enrique tierno galván, ceip ortiz echagüe, ies león felipe e ies ignacio aldecoa.

encuentro "ande yo valiente... #metoo getafense"  será hoy lunes 19n que coincide con el día internacional para la prevención del abuso sexual infantil. anunciaros que en la jornada del día 27 escucharemos testimonios sobre abuso sexual infantil. os iremos informando!

os esperamos hoy lunes 19 a las 18:30-20h en el @espaciomercadogetafe
plaza de la constitución, 28901, getafe. 
#getafe #metoo #amítambién #cuéntalo #asi #escúchales #getafe #25n #ies #ceip #participación #feminismo #igualdad #niunamenos #violenciasmachistas #cuartaola

text:
'currently, there are around 12 men a day in the uk that take their own life and suicide is the biggest killer of men under 35...'
.
today is international men's day and in the run up to this @thenationalstudent have been running a content series around male mental health featuring interviews, articles and artwork. as part of this mental health project i was asked to create an illustration to go alongside an article by jack mills about the importance of international men's day. it highlights the contraversy which often surrounds this day, especially in light of the #metoo movement, but discusses the ever growing need for it in today's society (head to thenationalstudent.com to read more)...
.
as this is an editorial piece it doesn't really need a title, but i titled it anyway. it's called 'boys cry too'... because for me, it was the take-home from the article. the fact that we must encourage a healthier view of crying/emotions/sadness in men and tell them it's not weakness, it's strength. it's strength to admit your not okay. it's strength to 'let it all out' and it's strength to seek help.
.
.
.
#boyscrytoo #malementalhealthawareness #malementalhealth #malesuicide  #internationalmensday2018 #internationalmensday #mentalhealthawareness #mencrytoo #seekhelp #editorialillustration #illustration #laurahopeillustration

text: plus de dix ans après leur parution, les romans de stieg larsson n’ont jamais été autant d’actualité : résurgence de l’extrême-droite, cyber-terrorisme, révolte féministe contre la bureaucratie et les prédateurs sexuels… de quoi se réjouir du come-back de la célèbre justicière dans notre monde post-#metoo. on espérait depuis 2011 une suite à millenium : les hommes qui n'aimaient pas les femmes, cauchemar envoûtant signé david fincher. mais les résultats décevants du film a contraint sony à rebooter la saga avec une nouvelle équipe. fede alvarez (le réalisateur de don’t breathe) succède à fincher, tandis que claire foy (concluant une année fructueuse, entre first man, paranoïa de soderbergh et son emmy award pour the crown) endosse la lourde tâche de faire oublier noomi rapace et rooney mara dans la peau de lisbeth. passé la scène d'introduction réussie, le récit delaissera vite le sous-texte féminin pourtant initié par alvarez pour laisser place à une histoire de menace nucléaire à la james bond d'une banalité déconcertante. on est sans surprise très loin de la maîtrise discrète et assurée de fincher, dont le spectre plane incontestablement sur ce nouveau volet. il n'y a plus cette violence sourde, plus d'ambiguïté, d'étrangeté et encore moins de travail sur la psychologie des personnages, en particulier sur l'antagoniste incarnée par sylvia hoeks, excellente en réplicante impitoyable dans blade runner 2049, qui ici peine à convaincre faute à une écriture paresseuse. millenium est devenu un thriller ordinaire, truffé de raccourcis et de scènes d'action aussi inutiles que mal-amenées. on sent tout de même l’envie d'alvarez de dynamiter le matériau de base avec quelques plans iconiques mais celui-ci se contente de recycler des idées visuelles déjà vues ailleurs (les étendues enneigées comme paysage mental, la moto esquivant les balles, la photographie froide) sans folie ni maestria. rempli de facilités scénaristiques et d'inerties informatiques (le talent d'hackeuse de lisbeth semble tout droit sorti du jeu vidéo watch dogs), ce qui ne me tue pas est un échec, un gâchis artistique et thématique comme rarement on en a vu au cinéma. hollywood a encore frappé. 5/10

scènes d'action aussi inutiles que mal-amenées. on sent tout de même l’envie d'alvarez de dynamiter le matériau de base avec quelques plans iconiques mais celui-ci se contente de recycler des idées visuelles déjà vues ailleurs (les étendues enneigées comme paysage mental, la moto esquivant les balles, la photographie froide) sans folie ni maestria. rempli de facilités scénaristiques et d'ineies informatiques (le talent d'hackeuse de lisbeth semble tout droit soi du jeu vidéo watch dogs), ce qui ne me tue pas est un échec, un gâchis aistique et thématique comme rarement on en a vu au cinéma. text:
in "#broke," @lecrae testifies to how poverty can make people wealthy. isn't that a #beautiful teaching? and how #sweet to see a #leader who makes sense!

we need our #prophets of #truth to displace the lie of profit.

this idea is central to the teachings of #decolonialbiznessworld. in decolonial bizness world, there's the soil of #natural #abundance at the base of the #treeoflife, which starts at the heart with #selflove  and includes #belovedcommunity and true love for #mothernature, who's now on #strike.

you see, when i'm not pushed into the position of having to call out #tech companies like #google, #facebook, and #linkedin for protecting #predators, i'm drawing upon community knowledge to help people decolonize business leadership so that we can transform a world system that creates financial poverty and profits from it.

as if that is the only form of violence at play in the world today. #4645boricuas.

in the case of #facebook, for example, a sexual predator or collection of them used my full legal name, darshan elena campos, to sell porn and sex via facebook for at least two months. i'll spare you all the details but this truth: facebook refused to remove the page. one day, it just disappeared. poof.

i have been locked out of posting images and videos to instagram since 4 july 2018 when i organized a free event, which asked what freedom means to native peoples, slaves, colonial subjects, and babies locked in a cage. i can't delete what's pending, and i can't log out either.

i am trapped.

i want to review the data trail. and, i want that personal and corporate information to be released to the digital commons so that we can figure out how to better respond to digitized sexual violence.

as for me, i also want to see the numbers in dollars and data so that i can design curriculum for decolonial bizness world on how ambitious social justice warriors such as myself can combat today's market failure of people trapped in similar situations. #metoo. i've been a victim, and i refuse to remain in the shadows. #timesup. i am not alone. #niunamenos.

here's a few other questions i have regarding this business case of digitized sexual violence: how much....

an insightful session on #metoo movement and prevailing legal regime, held at ansal university. it was a one-day workshop – ‘#metoo and beyond’, organized by the school of law and internal complaint committee of the university with an emphasis on prevention of sexual harassment (posh) act, 2013.

the inaugural ceremony was graced by hon’ble ms. rekha sharma, chairperson, national commission for women, prof. (dr.) g.s. bajpai (registrar, national law university, delhi), kanchan khatana, advocate & corporate trainer on posh, nilanjana jha cco, ht media, advocate mr. sanjeeb panigrahi, advocate-on-record, supreme court of india and prof. kanu piya acting dean, school of law. it was a much needed discussion on the future challenges and scenarios in the light of the current #metoo movement.

text:
"la lumiere des jours maudits". gorgeous violins by kathryn koch, bg vox by lena isabella, and costumes/sets provided by the amazing silvie. but tbh, the two men in this production (actor and director) were pretty awful to work with. i wrote, sang, engineered and co-produced the song, played all the guitars and bass, and yet i was treated like a fucking idiot by them. i would never again tolerate such disrespect. if i were a man in the same space, this would never have happened. they were french and delighted in mocking my american/aspie naivete. but, the darkness i felt translated well into the performance. 
why are women artists often treated so badly by the men who depend on them for so much? you can hear the song free on my soundcloud page, yt channel or buy on itunes under my old name.  #metoo #singersongwriter #femaleartist #girlswithguitars #girlswhoplayguitar #strongwomen #artemisiax #pennydreadful #pennydredful

text:
.
［什麼人是性罪犯］
.
有日男同事入校工作，不幸校方招募左成組女學生參加，老師即時問同事係咪已經做好「性罪行查核」。
.
十分有趣！
男性總被假設為侵犯者，
學校又會努力做好保護機制，
我們更會教好預防性侵犯....
但呂麗瑤事件敗數了，
又是怎樣一回事？
.
淨聽新聞演繹法官解釋，
講到事主：
1）當時為何唔出聲
2）年紀細（都15歲喇喎）未必清楚乜野係性侵
3）事主事後又同被告合照關係甚好
4）事主被#metoo運動影響
5）法庭不是倡議場所
.
再聽落去，加啲haters’ comments，
只會覺得呢個社會，冇得救！
.
做左查核又點，教育左又點，
攪咁多野，大家都係做左「免責機制」，根本唔係採取一切方法拒絕性暴力。
.
要blame the victim嘅，
要幾離譜有幾離譜！
.
#中女社工 
#metoo
#性罪行紀錄查核

text:
hi guys! i’ll be hosting/moderating a public forum tackling gender-based violence this nov 28 (wed), and would really appreciate the support :) registration is for free, message me if you can make it!

#metoo #timesup #donttellmehowtodress

join us for the #respetonaman forum at francisco santiago hall, bdo south tower, makati on november 28, 2018 from 5:30 to 8:00pm.

speakers include carla ocampo, writer and director of the film “walang rape sa bontok,” maritina romulo, of empower, councilor mayen juico, the champion of the safe cities and public spaces ordinance of quezon city, and charisse jordan of the un women safe cities metro manila programme. with special messages from ambassador harald fries of embassy of sweden in manila, and vp leni robredo

register at respetonaman.eventbrite.com

text_retweet:
#repost @bettansboktips 📚📚
titel: ”de kommer ändå inte tro mig”.
författare: ulla m. nissen
📚
elsa har flyttar och börjar på en ny skola. en fest ska hållas och för att kunna gå på den så ljuger hon för sina föräldrar att hon ska på tjejmiddag. på festen dras hon in i ett rum av en kille. elsa blir paralyserad och stänger av övergreppet. efteråt skäms hon. allt är hennes fel.
📚
en mycket viktig bok som jag hoppas att många läser, både yngre men även äldre. ett sätt att sätta sig in i hur tonårsflickor kan känna sig och hur de klandrar sig själva. så frustrerad jag blev, ”anmäl honom!!”. men hur gör man, som vän när man får höra något hemskt som hänt? hur pratar man som förälder när man ser att ens barn inte mår bra? så många frågor som väcktes. tyvärr en verklighet hos allt för många tjejer, hur de trycker ner sig själva och anser att något fruktansvärt som hänt är deras fel. jag blir så ledsen, och frustrerad, och arg. en mycket viktig bok! läs den som förälder och diskutera med andra föräldrar, och tonåringar, både tjejer och killar.
@u.m.nissen har skrivit en blandvändare om ett tungt ämne men blandar det med en fin berättelse om vänskap och tonårsförälskelse 💕

the traumatization of a child is a betrayal of their innocence. they have lost a unique part of themselves, which enables them to view the world from a perspective of wonder, joy and adventure which has been taken away from them.
.
trauma has a cumulative effective on children and can pervade their emotions for many years; and in some cases, their entire lives into adulthood.
.
you are not alone!
you are not a child anymore!
you can heal!
you can regain what has been unrightfully taken away from you!
.
.

text:
le 24 novembre prochain, à 14h00 à la madeleine.
j’y serai. 
en solidarité avec les femmes qui ont été ou sont harcelées, agressées, violées, tuées, chaque jour, ici et dans le monde.
ce mal endémique, systémique, nous entrave, nous blesse, s’attaque profondément à notre légitimité. individuelle. et collective. 
par le passé, il y a des siècles, en brûlant des femmes libres, sachantes et indépendantes, appelées parfois sorcières pour mieux les éliminer ; mais aujourd’hui encore, avec notamment le viol comme arme de guerre, le corps des femmes est un territoire politique dont les prédateurs ne cessent de vouloir prendre le contrôle. 
le 24 novembre à 14h00 à la madeleine, j’y serai aussi au nom de la petite et jeune fille, jeune femme, qui fut à différents moments de sa vie, agressée, forcée, harcelée sexuellement, dans la rue, dans un vestiaire, dans le rer, dans un appartement, dans un parti politique. 
grandir dès le plus jeune âge dans la peau d’une proie, comme #noustoutes, ne peut plus être une fatalité ! 
je refuse que ça le soit pour les générations futures. je crois aux vertus de l’éducation au consentement chez nos fils et filles dès le plus jeune âge. 
je crois fort à la libération de la parole pour mettre fin à l’ignominie de l’impunité. 
samedi, je marcherai la tête haute. 
nous ferons face symboliquement à ces agresseurs de nos passés, qui ont voulu nous soumettre à leur désir et délire de toute puissance.
nous dirons que ce fut vain puisque nous sommes là à dire notre dignité inaltérable de femmes debout.
nous dirons enfin que c’est ensemble, plus jamais isolées, que nous défendrons désormais l’intégrité de nos corps et de nos esprits. 
après toutes les marches féministes dans le monde, enfin, marcher en france. 
merci nous toutes
#metoo ✊️✊🏼✊🏾✊🏿

text:
#thisisnotconsent des de #barcelona 
me sumo a la 'revuelta del tanga' contra una sentencia absolutoria de violación en irlanda. las mujeres de irlanda están tomando las calles y las redes sociales con una campaña viral que, bajo la etiqueta #thisisnotconsent (esto no es consentimiento), protesta por la resolución de una sentencia judicial en un caso de violación.
la indignación por el trato que se da en este país a las supuestas víctimas de agresiones sexuales ha ido creciendo desde que esta semana un tribunal de la ciudad de cork (sur) absolvió a un hombre de 27 años que estaba acusado de violar a una joven de 17, tras una noche de fiesta.
la abogada del sospechoso, elizabeth o'connell, se refirió en su alegato final al tanga que llevaba la chica y pidió al jurado que lo tomara en consideración a la hora de emitir un veredicto, un planteamiento que ha llevado a grupos activistas y políticos a denunciar la "cultura que tiende a culpabilizar a las víctimas" en el sistema judicial.
"es necesario preguntarse si las pruebas descartan la posibilidad de que ella se sentía atraída por el acusado y estaba abierta a conocer a alguien y estar con alguien. hay que mirar la manera en que estaba vestida. llevaba un tanga con un lazo por delante", explicó la letrada. tras noventa minutos de deliberaciones, el jurado, compuesto por ocho hombres y cuatro mujeres, declaró al sospechoso "no culpable". #metoo #cuentalo #feminist #feminism #womensrights #women #girl #loveyourself #bcn

text: happy #internationalmensday to all the men who inspire me (you know who you are). it's still distressing to note that this day still isn't taken seriously. women's day gets plenty of recognition but men's day gets turned into a joke. in the era of the #metoo movement,  society comes out in full force for female victims but ridicule and mock male victims of harassment! we will only be equal as society when both genders are treated the same. if a woman uses her feminine wiles to get what she wants, no one cares. if a guy does the same, people lose their minds! why the double standards? in the age of girl power, a whole generation of boys have fallen on the wayside. to those guys, you are valued and not forgotten. to all the fellow guys out there, we need to redefine the outdated notion of masculinity and what it means to be a man in this day and age. no, the guy who prefers reading over sports is not a wimp! no, the guy who grooms and takes care of himself is not girly! no, the guy who wears florals and can't change a tyre isn't a sissy! we need to stop being defined by labels. the stay at home dad is not less of a man than the guy who is a ceo! we need to stop with the body shaming and the notion that six pack abs are the epitome of male beauty! a beard doesn't make you more of a man than the guy who doesn't have one.  if you are a gym addict, its cool. if you prefer curling up on the couch with popcorn, it's still cool. we need to revolt against magazines like @menshealthza who perpetuate the myth that you have to have abs carved out of granite and the looks of a greek god in order to be deemed successful! how about featuring a guy who isn't a slave to the gym or a regular dude on the cover for once? women's magazines are slowly changing from their unattainable beauty standards and it's time men's magazines followed suit. to all the guys, be yourself and stop worrying what society thinks of you!  don't let an outdated definition of masculinity define your life! 🙌 #proud #male #celebrate #truth #feelings #instamood #instalike #beyou #instapic #me #instagrammers #instagramhub #instadaily #awesome #love #igers #instagood #lifestyle #men #guy

text:
in every culture i have encountered (outside of western culture) there has been mythology, sacredology, surrounding women and the moon.

while living with #indigenous #women in #méxico i was taught for the first time about my cycle and what i can gain from it if i step towards it with curiosity instead of away from it with fear. 
in that curious journey i found that my cycle aligns with another most powerful lunar cycle, a gift from the universe, a whisper “you are bigger than you imagine! this body of yours, local, cumbersome, sick, is a ray of moonlight! you are a secret ceremony kept only for the grownups who stay up past dark, you are the worlds guiding light! you hold within you a rhythm of life and death that will be your greatest gift!” i stepped toward my next sacred and ancient culture with commitment and conviction in my #feminism. this feminism often did not and does not align with western liberal us feminism (and hey, ladies, that is okay!). i stepped toward the orthodox jewish wisdom around women, our cycle, and the jewish lunar solar cycle. this next step would change y perspective forever... more on that wisdom for another steep walk up the hill to work.
#doula #judaism #wisdom #inspiration #ithaca #jerusalem #kaballah

holding onto things that might happen in future

none of them are real 
how will long will take for me to survive?

text:
recension: "skammen är inte din" av anicia sundström eriksson (@aniciaeriksson)
❤
hjärtskärande hemsk, men åh så vacker - och viktig! ❤
anicias bagage, mörker och demoner har så många likheter med mina egna - den otrygga uppväxten, sjukdom och död i familjen, övergrepp, psykisk ohälsa, och den ständiga jakten på varje liten ljusglimt i allt det svarta. det gjorde att boken stundvis blev så övermäktigt tung att jag var tvungen att pausa läsningen, ibland i flera dagar. #metoo
❤
mörkret till trots skiner boken som en stjärna mot en nattsvart himmel, och ger hopp om att mörkret aldrig är oövervinnerligt.
❤
att boken är viktig har att göra med stigmatiseringen kring hemska upplevelser och psykisk ohälsa, och skulden som den utsatte och sjuke ofta lägger på sig själv. "skammen är inte din" syftar till att ge kunskap om ämnet, och att förändra samhällets föråldrade och fördomsfulla syn.
❤
du är fantastisk, anicia. att du vågar öppna ditt hjärta för alla att se, mitt i läkeprocessen, är så otroligt starkt. du imponerar och inspirerar, och jag tror stenhårt på att din bok kommer att kunna hjälpa andra. kanske är de vilse i mörkret, kanske har de börjat greppa efter ljuset, kanske är de ute på andra sidan av tunneln... oavsett så är "skammen är inte din" en bok som kan hjälpa till att läka en trasig själ.
❤
___

text:
min skörd av adlibris 5 för 99kr häromhelgen. minus en som blev slutsåld, plus en som ej var del av erbjudandet - så för min del blev det 5 för 133kr, vilket ändå inte är så illa.

pysselväskan blev genast en stor hit hos treåringen som nu roar sig med pusslet. väldigt trevlig liten samling!

anna gavalda fängslade mig med sina ord för många år sen, och har varit nyfiken på pajssällskapet sen jag först såg den. men "målarens musa" har jag ingen som helst koll på.

den där känslan, ändå, av nya böcker i hemmet 😍
▫️

text: this is lisa gabriele’s modern reimagining of daphne du maurier’s  gothic novel #rebecca, a classic first published in 1938, and has since, never been out of print. like the original, the story is told by an unnamed narrator, known only as the new/future mrs. winters who is swept away from her home on the #cayman islands 🇰🇾, by the rich and powerful max winters, to #asherley, his secluded estate in long island. rebekah winters, max’s first wife, has been dead for less then 2 years, having died in car accident on the road to asherley, burnt to a crisp, the only identifying feature her diamonds, in a pool of melted gold. in the original, the narrator’s nemesis is the infamous mrs. danvers, who is replaced by dani winters, a 15 yo bratty daughter to max. dani, appears to have it all, including 31k instagram followers, and like teens today, she is literally, attached to smartphone. where rebecca opens with the famous line: “last night i went to manderlley again”, gabriele opens the winters with a punch as well: “last night rebekah tried to murder me again”. lisa gabriel chose to retell rebecca for several reasons (from an interview). firstly, she grew up owning very few books but her mother had a copy of the original rebecca, so she read it many times, and she grew up watching hitchkok’s movie adaptation of the book, so it is a story extremely familiar to her. at the  time, the 2016 us election race was occurring, something that really was very upsetting to gabriele. so, it is no coincidence, that the rich max winters, is in politics (power). in her remake, (i do not want to spoil it), but gabriele shows, that today not just the powerful man’s story counts, but the woman’s story will be heard. #metoo. the novel is dedicated to lisa’s niece’s who provided the inspiration for dani winters. this is a great book. i highly recommend it. #bookoftheday #thewinters @lisagabrieletv #vikingbooks #gardinersbay #russianinterference #research #longisland #mrsdanvers #hitchcock #roses 🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹

text: thank you to all the beautiful women (& baby max!), who came out to our first @_rehumanize empowerment event ✨ deeply grateful to have co-created this gathering with soul sister & mindful belly moves magic-maker, s’ya 🔮 such power when women come together. it was an honour to facilitate discussion around the ripple-outward affect of this ‘work’. embodied activism 🎉 we are literally breaking down objectification culture, with every hip roll & every breath that brings us back to our bodies/centres. shifting from performance back to feeling because: a) it feels good, b) our culture shapes our relation to our bodies, just as much as our relation to our bodies shapes our culture 😍 infinite gratitude for this dharma-paved path. more #rehumanize magic to come!

children have the right to withhold affection from whomever they wish with no explanation. allowing children to create boundaries and develop body autonomy at an early age can help them protect themselves from predatory behavior. children have great instincts and intuition about adults, and when allowed to lean into them, they will create immediate boundaries between themselves and people they don't get a good feeling about. when you force affection, you not only chip away at these instincts and intuition, but you also subconsciously tell them they have no control over their bodies; who touches them, and you override the requirements for permission and consent. predators can easily manipulate a child into believing that sexual abuse is ok when the child's ability to create boundaries and body autonomy has been eroded away by forced affection, especially when it is their main caregivers who are forcing them to be affectionate with other adults. and, while many parents and caregivers somehow take on a feeling of embarrassment when their child withholds affection from someone they feel they should otherwise be affectionate towards, just consider how as an adult you aren't always in the mood to hug and kiss other people and how offensive it would be if you were forced to do so after you've already said no. remember, children are little people with feelings just like adults and we must respect them just as we demand respect of our own feelings by other adults. so, this thanksgiving when your child says no to hugging or kissing grandma, grandpa, uncle, aunty, or cousin whomever, let it go! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text: idag är det internationella mansdagen och istället för att ge männen min dagliga dos uppläxning då de behöver skärpa till sig så vill jag istället idag ge alla de män som finns i mitt liv, har funnits och kommer att finnas en stor eloge. alla de män som är föredömen. all de män som står upp, behandlar en med respekt och ser oss kvinnor. män som calle, en man som gladeligen bär min krans, väska samtidigt som han låter mig ta exakt så mycket plats jag vill. eller ulf, en man som redan från dag ett för 20 år sedan öppnade sin famn och tog sig ann mig som sin dotter, blodsband eller ej. jag vill hylla mannen som höll upp dörren åt mig tidigare idag och pojken som förra veckan tog sin systerns hand när hon var ledsen på tunnelbanan. jag vill hylla er män som har skärpt till er efter #metoo stormen och alla er som tar kampen mot de som har en bit kvar. jag älskar män. ni är fantastiska. inte alltid. hell no. men nästan.

text: hey y’all, i just wanted to give you an update. earlier this week i posted about what people were saying about this one guy i have need talking to recently and i ended up talking to him in person last night and overall i think it went really well. i explained that i wanted a relationship, but respect the fact that he doesn’t and i want to be friends with him, however i don’t want to hook up with him because i don’t want to be just some hook up to him. we ended up cuddling and even though i had doubts about him based off of what other people have said, he was very nice. he kept wanting to hook up and respected when i said no. i had fun hanging out with him and as a result we are going to just be friends. we also had a chance do discuss what i’ve heard about him and i apologized for judging him based on what others said and explained that it just made me nervous and want to be cautious which he understood. thank you to those who continue to support me as it really means a lot and i hope you guys know i’m here for you too and if you have any questions, don’t be afraid to ask. ❤️-rissy  #love #youareenough #loveyourselffirst #quotes #quotesdaily #inspiration #sexualassault #empowerment  #survivor #metoo #metoomovement #recovery #feminist #feminism #feministquote  #trauma #female #inspirationalquote #equality #trigger #triggerwarning #assault #ptsd #mybodymychoice #consent #endrapeculture #timesup #depression #anxiety
