text: "'sisterhood' is inspired by women across the world. #metoo has sparked a fire within women tired of being oppressed. whether it's through the policing of bodies, the colour of skin, sexuality, religion, sexual and physical violence, fgm, access to education or having fewer political, social, and economic rights, women suffer every day at the hands of men. nothing draws people together like pain and my poem highlights that together, women hold immense power. by speaking out and supporting one another, we can create real change."

text:
i am personally terrible at this because i am so socially awkward (just ask @rebelsoulloyalheart how badly i fail when trying to interact with the opposite sex 🙈). on top of that people always think i am interested when i am not, because i am friendly.  and i am almost always clueless when someone is interested in me 🤦🏼‍♀️🤷🏼‍♀️
but i digress.  i wanted to talk a little bit about double standards.  i had someone reach out recently doubting herself and her decision to give her phone number to a man.  she was mostly doubting herself because people she knew were making her feel like she had made a bad decision.  i vehemently disagreed.  i thought her choice was fabulous.  now don’t get me wrong, i am still quite traditional in my views and told her to now sit back and let him take the lead by planning and paying for the first date.  i personally believe in more traditional gender roles.  but i also believe we have made dating really hard for men.  many women are very harsh to men who ask them out if they are not interested.  men are still told to man up, take care of women, etc. but women are also shouting about equality and the #metoo movement and forgetting how to be kind humans when a man is brave enough to ask her out.  now as i mentioned earlier basic dating rules still apply once you’ve passed your number on; he should text or preferably call within a reasonable amount of time to get to know you better and set up a date, he should plan and pay for that date, he should be consistent, reliable, and share your morals and values, etc.
it must be frustrating to be a man where women can be incredibly rude if you express interest, and where many women want equality but not when it comes to dating.  ladies make it a tiny bit easier on both of you and do not be scared to make the first move and suggest coffee sometime or give him your number.  and here is the biggest part: do it without expectation. if he does not like you?  or he never calls?  that is not a reflection of you or your worth!!! he doesn’t even really know you yet so his refusal to do so does not in any way make you unworthy of love ❤️ .
.
.
.
.
#dating #datingadvice #personaldevelopment #bebold

text_retweet:
#repost @rapesurvivorsupport ・・・
what survivors are really asking for when they want to be believed:
it’s important to remember, believing a survivor does not begin and end with simply believing that they have been raped.

believing them must extend to believing their symptoms, believing their experience, believing that they are trying their best, even when you can’t understand how this bright, previously successful person’s new ‘best’ could possibly be as basic as leaving the house that day.

this idea that strength means remaining unaffected is pervasive, but ridiculous. strength is fully acknowledging how horrible your experience was, and choosing to live, anyway. just because i’m here and speaking out today doesn’t mean i’m okay. i was shocked to lose so much of what i had once thought was unchangeable about myself. everything changed, and i would have begun to heal so much sooner had i not tried so hard to force myself into being fine. i was not fine, and i had the right to be broken, because someone tried to break me.
.
.
.

text:
if i could cry,
in front of peeps.
my tears would recite 
a story of every men
who wish to cry
but instead, 
pressed the neck
of their emotions 
as it renders them as weak.

if i could cry,
my eyes would showcase
a film of every boy
who was ignored because 
trusting men is a crime.
they hurt you,
they are dogs,
they play.
as if inhuman and men
are synonyms.

if i could cry,
my tear stains would
write unsaid 
words of grief,
from a boy 
who was cheated
and claimed as "boys
prefer skin over hearts."
.
if i could cry,
i would plead,
scream and shout
to the world
that even we are humans 
hiding our emotions
underneath our hard skin.

we do get hurt.
we do feel lonely.
we do care.
we do
love.

if i could cry,
i will,
behind a closed door.

it's just that our 
tears are not seen.

darshan sanghvi.
(@darshansanghvi28)
.

name: Beyond thoughts
tweet_full:
if i could cry,
in front of peeps.
my tears would recite 
a story of every men
who wish to cry
but instead, 
pressed the neck
of their emotions 
as it renders them as weak.

if i could cry,
my eyes would showcase
a film of every boy
who was ignored because 
trusting men is a crime.
they hurt you,
they are dogs,
they play.
as if inhuman and men
are synonyms.

if i could cry,
my tear stains would
write unsaid 
words of grief,
from a boy 
who was cheated
and claimed as "boys
prefer skin over hearts."
.
if i could cry,
i would plead,
scream and shout
to the world
that even we are humans 
hiding our emotions
underneath our hard skin.

we do get hurt.
we do feel lonely.
we do care.
we do
love.

if i could cry,
i will,
behind a closed door.

it is just that our 
tears are not seen.

darshan sanghvi.
(@darshansanghvi28)
.
.
.

text:
japon 🇯🇵. ▶️ shiori ito, le symbole du mouvement #metoo au japon. ▶️ en mai 2017, lors d’une conférence de presse, shiori ito déclare avoir été droguée et violée en 2015 par un journaliste de renom, proche du premier ministre shinzo abe, noriyuki yamaguchi.
▶️ l’histoire de shiori ito a été rendue publique en mai 2017 : elle est l’une des premières victimes à avoir pris la parole publiquement, pour dénoncer non seulement son violeur, mais aussi tout le système administratif japonais dans la prise en charge des victimes de viols. ▶️ elle est ainsi devenue l’une des figures emblématiques du combat contre les agressions sexuelles au japon.
#oenddf #metoo #japan #tokyo #droitsfondamentaux  #fundamentalrights #globalfundforwomen
#droitsdesfemmes #womenrights #humanrights #empowerment #globalgoals #genderequality #freedom #liberté #sexualviolence

• gainesville police department, 911 or 352-393-7500 or www.reportrapegainesville.com
• uf health shands emergency room, 352-733-0800
• alachua county victim services, 352-264-6760
• peaceful paths, 352-377-8255 or 1-800-500-1119
• alachua county crisis center, 352-264-6789
• three rivers legal services, 352-372-0519

university of florida resources: • uf police department office of victim services, 352-392-1111 or 352-392-5648 (non-emergency)
• uf student health care center, 352-392-1161
• uf counseling and wellness center, 352-392-575
• u matter, we care, 352-294-2273
• uf student legal services, 352-392-5297 • intimate partner violence assistance clinic, 352-273-0805
• strive at gatorwell, 352-273-4450 .
.
.

i never spent much time thinking about what life would be like after i left, because i never saw a way out. i was naive enough to think leaving would be the hardest part and once i did that everything would get easier. 🙄 if i had only known then what i know now. the effects of being in a long term dv relationship/marriage are lifelong. the damage is there. it is always there. with a lot of inner work, therapy and support things do get better. but you do leave forever changed. complex ptsd is not a joke. it's not an easy thing to learn to live with. i had a very busy week.  too busy infact. i had a lot of triggers and a few flashbacks.  like any illness or injury,  when you're tired your symptoms get worse. last night i was in tears. i can't even say why. it's just like my brain can only process so much and once i have reached my limit, i start shutting down,  checking out emotionally.  i just want to be alone. but i don't want to be alone. i can't process any more information.  noise, lights, temperature,  everything can bother me. usually when i get to this place i  tell my family my ptsd is triggered and my brain needs a break. unfortunately,  the rest of the world doesn't care if this is what's going on internally. i just look dramatic or lazy, attention seeking etc. in reality i am just trying to keep myself together.  some days are just hard. and sometimes it's everyday stress that is too overwhelming. i haven't been able to convince myself that i am  safe.... but then again, maybe it's because as long as he is out there, i am not.  so for tonight, i will do self care. tomorrow as well. letting myself have a break from my reality and just focus on getting through each moment. stay strong with me 💜

para nosotros es fundamental recordar que como adultos debemos proteger a nuestros niños, niñas y adolescentes, debemos hablarles, escucharlos, tender puentes de comunicación para que sientan la confianza y la libertad de preguntarnos y decirnos cualquier cosa que les inquiete. es por eso que contamos con el apoyo de @paulabevilacqua actriz venezolana para recordarle al mundo que la prevención es la única solución para #quenopasemás.

text:
👇see these? these are my pills- my anti-depressants.💊 .. .

some people have this preconceived notion that they are failures if they take medication. a lot of people want to do it in a more natural way. .

great! that is fantastic. 🙌 i am so happy that you are taking steps on a more natural lifestyle. but i will say. medication doesn't make you a failure. .

before i had medication it would take everything that i had to get out of bed. when i did it was for my children, but i often glued my butt to my chair, where i cried. a lot. .

throughout the day i would have severe panic attacks thinking about what horrible of a mother and wife i was. i would look at all the things around the house that needed to be done, and i would become so overwhelmed that i would crawl back to my chair and cry. .

medication was a game changer. i was starting to be able to do things again and spend more time with my children and my husband. but still, something wasn't right. .

i finally was sent to see my psychiatrist where he put me on my other pill. wow, what a game changer. .

i can smile, and get out of bed and do things, my panic attacks have lessened. i am now able to focus on the natural path that i am so passionate about. .

i am able to get up to go to therapy, go buy healthy food, i can spend time with my kids. .

does taking medication make me a failure? i smile, i am happy, i clean the house, i go on outings, i play with my children. i am not glued to a chair? i run a business? .

heck no. 💯 it didn't make me a failure. .

it made me successful. .

the first step is scary. but the most rewarding. .

text:
this. this is what it comes down to for me.

i am not defined by what has happened to be, rather what has happened to me is part of my story. i do not find my identity in what happened to me, but rather i find my identity in christ and who i choose to be.

i am stronger, more resilient, empathetic and compassionate because of what i have experienced. i made the choice early in my healing journey, to become the best version of me despite the pain, trauma and heartache i was experiencing and feeling simultaneously.

healing and becoming your best you, is not an easy task, commitment or journey. but it's possible, attainable and living giving.

are you ready for it? and will you keep going no matter how hard it can get?

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
trigger warning to anyone who has dealt with sexual trauma. .
.
can we stop sexualizing non-con and abuse? it's not "relationship goals" it's not "owo so hot and kinky". no. it's disgusting. romanticizing and fetishizing the pain and suffering of others is wrong. i cant say it any more clearly. it feeds those who commit these atrocities and it gives them a reason to believe they are not in the wrong, when they are. i know plenty of wonderful people who are sadly traumatized and had their lives forever changed by terrible people and their acts. and rather than helping, others just see it as a way to live out their distorted sexual fantasies. hitting your significant other is not justified. forcing yourself onto someone is not justified. and taking up for them and treating their actions like fuel for your twisted desires is no better. .
if you are or have been sexually, physically, or emotionally traumatized and you need someone dont be afraid to reach out. there is someone there for you. be it a friend, family, hotline, therapist, or hell even me if your desperate enough. someone is there to listen and help you through this. you deserve a life better than this. don't let it be the end of your story, because then they have won. you have to stay strong. you've got this.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
can getting fired be ... good for your career? a 10-year study of over 2,600 leaders showed that 45% of them had at least one major career blow-up — like getting fired, messing up a major deal, or blowing an acquisition. despite this, 78% eventually become ceos. additional research found that 18% of 360 executives had been fired or laid off — but 68% landed a new job within six months, and 91% took a job similar to or more senior than their last. these leaders did a few things that contributed to their success: (1) they looked facts in the face. if they were fired for performance reasons, for example, they accepted it and talked about learning from it. (2) they leaned on their professional networks to get a new job. (3) they looked for jobs in industries where they had experience, rather than jumping to something new. .
via @harvard_business_review
credit: blaise hayward/getty images

text:
here we go! tonight's the night of our first community roundtable discussion. this time it is about sexual assault. 
i wonder if the kavanaugh hearings and #metoo will be talked about this holiday season? how do we have these conversations without it destroying the day? without it tearing down relationships? we need to learn how to listen and to provide space for view points that don't align with our own. this is where we learn the most.
excited to learn from tonight's discussion. can't wait to share the important take aways.
love and light! 🌈🌸💕

text:
say hello to amanda! thank you so much for sharing your story with us!
.
hi! my name is amanda, i struggled with body image & an eating disorder early on in life, had a #metoo event in high school, struggled with anxiety, depression & suicidal tendencies and finally hit rock bottom in 2014! at that point it was either my life or “my life”. so against all odds, i decided to redesign my entire life! i quit my job in finance, separated from my husband, went into a 4 month outpatient recovery program called recovery road in santa barbara, california and started to rebuild! .
now i can happily say i’ve been sober for over 4 years as of october 2014! i’m also now a model/actor, inspirational speaker, body positive advocate, social media influencer, i work for @fabuplus and have 71,000 followers on instagram! and my message to those of you reading this is that you can change your life at anytime! at any age! and go after your dreams! i believe you have the strength to get sober and let me just say #soberissexy 😊 #loveyou
name: Soberocity

text:
-
프로필에 청원있습니다. 청원 널리퍼뜨려주세요.
-
오늘 해군대위에 대한 성폭력 최초가해자 2심 선고 방청에 다녀왔습니다. 1심에서 가해자 두명 각 8년, 10년 형을 선고 받았지만 어이없게도 오늘 2심 고등군사법무부는 두명의 가해자에게 무죄판결을 내렸습니다. 
재판관은 성폭력 피해자의 심리상태에 대한 수많은 사례들이 있음에도 불구하고 판결과정에 첨삭하지않고 가해자가 ‘피해자가 저항하지 않았다.’라는 주장만을 거듭 강조했습니다. 또한 군사고등대법원장이 직접 판결내리는 재판이었음에도 불구하고 군부대 출입 가능한 기자들은 오지않았다는 점도 내부의 입김이있지않았나 의구심이듭니다.
#국민청원 #성폭력 #성폭력근절 #군대 #군인 #여군 #탈코르셋 #탈코 #탈코전시 #oodt #metoo #미투 #미투운동 #한국성폭력상담소

text:
#danienlaonu
estamos orgullosos de la participacion de daniela en la onu en el marco de la conmemoración oficial del día internacional de la eliminación de la violencia contra la mujer, que se celebra en la sede de las naciones unidas en nueva york.

daniela giuliano, quien asiste a la granja andar desde hace 10 años, ha sido invitada a las naciones unidas por la directora ejecutiva de onu mujeres, la sra. phumzile mlambo-ngcuka, junto a sandra vazquez de casa fusa.

cabe señalar que daniela, sera una de las ciento de mujeres que participara del proyecto "desear (derechos sexuales en argentina) con inclusión, "promoviendo el acceso a los derechos sexuales y reproductivos de mujeres y niñas con discapacidades en argentina", que lleva adelante la red por los derechos de las personas con discapacidad (redi). a través de esta iniciativa "se podrá profundizar y expandir los esfuerzos por empoderar a un número creciente de mujeres, niñas y adolescentes con discapacidad de diversas regiones del país, quienes al final de esta iniciativa contarán con información y herramientas de calidad que les permitirán ejercer sus derechos y, al mismo tiempo, actuar como agentes de cambio y empoderamiento de otras mujeres con discapacidad". #metoo #timesup #niunamenos #notonemore #balancetonporc #escuchametambien #pintaelmundodenaranja #16días #escúchametambién #untf

text:
alison pollard-mansergh, company artistic director & co-founder, australia
.
i’ve experienced bullying throughout my life, at school, at work, and online. it affects who you are as a person, it makes you question what it is about you that deserves this treatment, it gets into your head and stays there. i’m also a cancer survivor. fighting cancer is horrific, but the long-term effects of bullying in many instances are worse. however, i refuse to be a victim, and don’t tolerate bullying in any form and encourage others not to be silent. let’s shine a spotlight on this crime forever, not just a week.
.
#antibullying #antibullyingweek #theatre #harassment #standup #metoo #notinourindustry #stopbullying #bullyingawareness #mentalhealth

text:
cos'è il consenso? non è poi una domanda così banale a giudicare dal numero di stupratori assolti, negli anni. è una domanda che si affaccia presuntuosa dal momento in cui il #metoo moviment ha fatto la sua comparsa nelle piazze del mondo. ebbene il consenso innanzitutto è libertà: devo dire sì, senza minacce, coercizione e paura. il consenso deve essere reversibile: posso dirti sì e poi decidere che non mi va in un altro momento. deve essere informato: devo dire sì, nella totale certezza di cosa sta per succedere di lì a poco. il consenso è entusiasta: se ho voglia di fare qualcosa non ho bisogno di inutili giri di parole per dire "ssììì". il consenso - infine - è specifico: se accetto di uscire con te, non è implicito che tu debba portarmi a letto.
e soprattutto il consenso è consenso, ossia "sentire insieme". perché se il "sì" lo sente solo uno dei due, non vale.
[immagine dal web]

#consenso #consent #femminismo #feminism #inspiration #girl #girls #girlpower #ragazzesexy #ragazze #woman #women #donneitaliane #donna

tack fina @maria_walsater för dessa ord, gjorde hela min dag ❤️
-
-
repost from @maria_walsater using @repostregramapp - recension: "skammen är inte din" av anicia sundström eriksson (@aniciaeriksson)
❤
hjärtskärande hemsk, men åh så vacker - och viktig! ❤
anicias bagage, mörker och demoner har så många likheter med mina egna - den otrygga uppväxten, sjukdom och död i familjen, övergrepp, psykisk ohälsa, och den ständiga jakten på varje liten ljusglimt i allt det svarta. det gjorde att boken stundvis blev så övermäktigt tung att jag var tvungen att pausa läsningen, ibland i flera dagar. #metoo
❤
mörkret till trots skiner boken som en stjärna mot en nattsvart himmel, och ger hopp om att mörkret aldrig är oövervinnerligt.
❤
att boken är viktig har att göra med stigmatiseringen kring hemska upplevelser och psykisk ohälsa, och skulden som den utsatte och sjuke ofta lägger på sig själv. "skammen är inte din" syftar till att ge kunskap om ämnet, och att förändra samhällets föråldrade och fördomsfulla syn.
❤
du är fantastisk, anicia. att du vågar öppna ditt hjärta för alla att se, mitt i läkeprocessen, är så otroligt starkt. du imponerar och inspirerar, och jag tror stenhårt på att din bok kommer att kunna hjälpa andra. kanske är de vilse i mörkret, kanske har de börjat greppa efter ljuset, kanske är de ute på andra sidan av tunneln... oavsett så är "skammen är inte din" en bok som kan hjälpa till att läka en trasig själ.
❤
___

text:
big freaking news:

i’m not one for long captions but this is important so bear with me. 
almost a year ago i went through the most traumatic experience of my life. in the past 11 months, it has taken everything i have to hold myself together. i’m not one to share personal information on social media, but i’m taking this opportunity to share some of my most personal thoughts and feelings with the public. i am now ready to share my experience with the world in hopes that it does some sort of good. the cigarette diaries ep is my chance to prove to myself that i am capable of living life the the fullest and my chance to prove to the world that i’ve got this. 2019 will be the year of no more fear, no more anxiety, no more depression, and no more bullshit excuses. #metoo

text: che animale è #ocean8 ?e’ un heist-movie in salsa #metoo o un #sexandthecity "aggiornato" in cui, per comprarsi delle manolo blahnik in tempi di crisi, le girls sono costrette a sgraffignare una collana di pietre preziose? e non pietre preziose qualsiasi, ma diamanti. e certo, perché, come cantavano #marylinmonroe e #janerussell ne #gliuominipreferisconolebionde , "i diamanti sono i migliori amici delle ragazze", e quindi come resistere? certamente la somiglianza fra la variante in gonnella di #oceaneleven , #twelve e #thirteen e la serie con protagoniste carrie, charlotte, samantha e miranda c’è, e ci sono i riferimenti a tante new york stories al femminile, a cominciare da #ildiavolovesteprada , al quale è impossibile non pensare quando la macchina da presa di #garyross indugia felicemente su un immenso armadio pieno di scarpe. ma anche una celebrazione del "girl power" è ben presente, e che risponda a un’intenzione programmatica o a una inconsapevole influenza dei tempi che cambiano, non possiamo dirlo con esattezza, sebbene una battuta pronunciata mentre le sette rapinatrici progettano il colpo ci fa propendere per la prima ipotesi. quando debbie ocean dice: "un lui viene notato, una lei no", il messaggio che arriva, seppure in un contesto di leggerezza e di intrattenimento, è il seguente: le donne possono essere invisibili, talmente invisibili da rubare un gioiello da 150 milioni di dollari senza che nessuno se ne accorga, cosa che nel film assicura la riuscita della losca impresa, perché le nostre ladre arrivano a muoversi indisturbate nel metropolitan museum di new york. e però, e per fortuna, capita che le nostre arsenio lupin ogni tanto mostrino qualche debolezza, che non resistano, per esempio, alla seduzione di abiti da sera dorati o in stile glam rock, tanto più se l’occasione in cui sfoggiarli è il met gala, evento a cui ogni fashion victim guarda con ammirazione estatica, perché vedersi passare davanti anna wintour in uno dei musei più prestigiosi del mondo è un privilegio a dir poco squisito. #movie

text: building on the momentum of global movements and grassroots campaigns such as "#metoo", “#timesup”, “#balancetonporc”, “#niunamenos”, "#metooindia" and “hollaback!”, the @unitednations theme for this year’s #16days of activism against gender-based violence (25 november – 10 december) under the unite to end violence against women campaign is "orange the world: #hearmetoo." #hearmetoo brings to the forefront the voices of women and girls who have survived violence, who are defending women’s rights every day, who are taking action — many of them very far away from the limelight or media headlines. their voices and stories must be heard, too. here are some pictures from today’s commemoration!

text:
where is it? is it hidden behind the bushes? or behind that make-up, you put on? or is it hidden under your fancy dress? or is it there, under your high heel?
oohh sorry, i forgot! it was available on women's day only.
we live in a world that is full of #hypocrites. i am one among them! yeah, #metoo , in fact, you too, and you and you standing distant from me and the one hiding behind the door.
i am not a #feminist nor a masculinist (if such a term exists). all i am is women who #respect men but (i told you, i am a hypocrite) without keeping aside my own self-respect.
i have a clear picture of how to treat who and how to behave with whom. i respect men when they respect my thoughts. i respect men who make me feel comfortable in their company, even if we are digitally conversing. i respect men who know what a men need to be. i respect men who are as free as air and let their counterpart be the same. i respect men who do not scan me out when i wear those fitted clothes.
you know, when you talk about #equality, get it for everyone! try and figure out that like you think for your rights likewise the other person looks for his/her rights.
why do a men need to stand up and offer you a seat? ok fine, it is a #ladies only seat, but then what if he had a more hectic day in office then you? why do only he need to stand up when you need a seat? well some of them are just real gentlemen and stand up by their own selves but the ones who don't are not culprits. they are just trying to equalize everything! the balance you see?
the thing is "women empowerment does not lie in a seat reserved for ladies". it lies in the basic fact of understanding and treating men as your equals. treat them as men and not culprits. compliment them when you feel like as it is not only their keen responsibility to praise you. take them out on a date. be their shoulder on which they can pour out that heavy heart. console them that things are going to be okay. hold their hand when everyone else is leaving them alone in a crowd. make them feel special and wanted when they have nothing with them.
women, if there is a code of being a gentlemen than let me remind you, there is a code of being a lady to

text:
this is a glimpse of a feature i wrote in the july 2017 issue of image magazine (@image.ie). i was really proud of it; i wrote of my disability and how film and its various depictions of disabilities ultimately inspired me to feel good about my own sense of self confidence and body image. looking back, in so many years of having the mild cerebral palsy (cp), it’s only the third article i’ve written on it - and my first ever in print. 
this fact makes me feel very shameful, how little i’ve actively done to spread the message for other women with similar mobility issues. and then there’s the guilt: look how much more i could be doing to use the platform i have as a writer to offer some semblance of comfort to others? i had no one growing up, a part from my incredible mother who i felt truly understood, who could say, ‘i know exactly what you’re going through.’ and if i could offer that to any young woman (in any small way) feeling as i do, i’d be thrilled. 
the truth is, it’s taken me 31 years to feel fully comfortable speaking really publicly about my cp, to feel that i wouldn’t be boxed in or labelled or held back in some way if i did so. but 2018 has made me feel differently. 
i look at all the women so bravely trying to make a change; fighting against #metoo, unafraid to speak out and i know i should be joining them, doing something instead of feeling furious that more isn’t done to champion women and disabilities in ireland. wondering why so many conversations on #ableism don’t include those directly affected by it. so, i’m starting now. really starting. a bit late, but better late than never. my cp is on all my platforms and i want to talk and write about it more so that it might help others. and i figure here is as good a place as any. 
sorry for the mini-rant and a huge thanks to @image.ie and the team for letting me write the piece (you can read the full thing by following the link in my bio) and for all their support generally as i try to navigate a world of publishing that was made with fully-able bodied people in mind! the same goes for my wonderful family and friends, none of whom i could tackle daily life with the ease i try to without them 💛

text:
today is a big big day for women’s rights in scotland.

i visited my solicitor in glasgow and received the news that stephen coxen is not appealing the decision from the sheriff that he raped me. the appeal period is now over, so it is official. 
it took 5 years for someone to acknowledge that what he did was wrong and unlawful. 
i will continue to fight for other women and i hope that this verdict brings hope to others. 
#fightingforjustice 
#metoo #rapesurvivor #rapevictim #rape #missm #fighter #survivor #womensrights #rapecrisis

text:
i don’t just hear the one off story. since my attack i’ve heard about 50, mostly of people i know as opposed to famous people. 
every story is a strong trigger that puts me back to where they are and what they are feeling. i’m not saying i don’t want people to tell me it has happened to them, im so blessed to be trusted with people stories. but every time i hear about something, it really does pull my mind and body back, i take a while to recover from it. 
#rapesurvivor #metoo

text:
my whole reason of becoming a coach is because i want to help others improve their lifestyle and help build self confidence in others that struggle to know that you can do whatever you put your mind to. -
in this picture that i was just bullied & criticized for being a “crackhead, no titties, no ass etc “ 😂🤣 i was 130-140lb & my weight gain went to my face, my stomach , thighs etc. the pic on the right is from over a couple months ago when i started my health and fitness journey. i had dropped down to 100lbs from anxiety and depression. people want to say i’m a “crackhead” and need to get “sober”. guess what!? none of that is true. truth is: i was fat and didn’t feel good about myself so i made a change. what’s wrong with that!? 🤷🏽‍♀️ #learnyourfacts -
i was thinking about what to post today & since i’m real i’m going to explain how an individual that doesn’t get his way thinks that he can try and bully me through a situation. guess what!? i’m a smart & strong woman that knows right from wrong, knows that lies said against me aren’t going to hurt me because i have confidence in my self & have matured to not let things bug me like they used to. -
listen, bullies never win! the best way to beat a bully is to punch him in the mouth to shut him up. it is very immature of a male to think that he can call a female a crackhead, verbally threaten and slander you when you have done nothing wrong. it is disgusting how men talk to women and think they can get away with it. especially when they are being called out on their shit and don’t want to own up for their actions/mistakes but instead blame and bully. i’m sorry but #metoo movements are created because of you sick minded people. females, like myself, are sick & tired of being attacked for doing the right thing. i’m here to inspire others to stand up for your rights & for what you believe in because that’s going to help you get you through life. you can’t be scared or keep quiet. speak loudly that #bullyingfemales is not allowed. i hope this helps ya’ll 🤗 #stopbullying

text: at one point in my life i would paint my random lovers immediately after our first time. it was a way for me to capture a form of magic we long to keep fresh in our minds. a feeling of lust and nervousness, school yard crushes, and makeout sessions behind the gym. the exploring another person so new to your life in such an intimate way. that is what life is meant for. #art #fineart #highendart #fem #artwork #modernart #contemporaryart #abstractart #streetart #jacksonpollock #acrylic #paint #paintdrip #instaart #neonjesusart #love #glitter #glitterwhore #namaste #freethenipple #feminism #metoo #beauty #mua #loa #positivevibes #positivity #bethelight #spreadlove #purpose

text:
hoy es un buen día para hablar de lo que no se suele hablar... hablemos del abuso sexual infantil (asi): @regran_ed from @hablafundacion - ¿conoces los tipos de abusosexualinfantil? ⭕ abuso sexual: cualquier forma de contacto físico con o sin acceso carnal, realizado sin violencia o intimidación y sin consentimiento. puede incluir: penetración vaginal, oral y anal, penetración digital, caricias o proposiciones verbales explícitas. ⭕ agresión sexual: cualquier forma de contacto físico con o sin acceso carnal con violencia o intimidación y sin consentimiento. ⭕ exhibicionismo: es un tipo de abuso sexual sin contacto físico que consiste en la exposición del cuerpo –de la persona agresora o de la víctima- con francas intenciones sexuales. ⭕ exposición: es la forma de abuso sexual infantil sin contacto físico, que incluye la exposición de niños o niñas a material pornográfico, la manipulación vía internet de niños o niñas para la producción de material visual de contenido sexual. ⭕ explotación sexual infantil: es un tipo de abuso sexual infantil en el que el abusador persigue un beneficio económico, engloba la prostitución y la pornografía infantil. se consideran tipos de explotación sexual infantil el tráfico sexual infantil, el turismo sexual infantil, la prostitución infantil, la pornografía infantil.

text: in addition to her own brave personal narrative, harriet employs interviews with others who are estranged, as well as recent research on family estrangement in order to open up discourse on the emotional experience that is estrangement. it is a thoughtful, deeply researched, and engaging exploration of the ties that bind and break, forgiveness, reconciliation, and what family really means. it is a must read for anyone with tangled family relations. learn more about #shadowdaughter by #harrietbrown at feministwednesday.com #feminist #womeninfilm #feminism #timesup #metoo #feministaf #feministwednesday #vivalabeaver #girlboss #letsgo #bettythebeaver #wednesdayvibes #mybodymychoice #feminista #getitgirl #whorinstheworld #beavertalk #resist #wcw #humpday #girlpower #empowerment #wedinspo #wednesday #slayallday #letsgogirls #brooklyn #girlsrule

text:
divisé en trois parties : de 1789 à 1860, de 1860 à 1945, de 1945 à 2000, ce petit livre de 120 pages dans la collection @coll_quesaisje permet de mieux comprendre le féminisme et ses différents mouvements à travers les pays et les époques. 
politique, droits, éducation, genre, culture, racisation... l'évolution du féminisme et de sa séparation en plusieurs mouvements à travers les années et sur les différents continents est expliqué. 
florence rochefort, historienne, codirigeante de la revue clio, femmes, genre et histoire, est spécialiste de l'histoire des féminismes,  des femmes et du genre. elle nous explique ces différents féminismes, leurs évolutions et inégalités.
c'est très intéressant et cela permet de mieux comprendre le féminisme d'aujourd'hui, ainsi que les différents courants. 
en conclusion, elle nous rappelle que le féminisme et son combat sont toujours d'actualité notamment grâce aux réseaux sociaux avec "les blogueuses des révolutions arabes, le phénomène #metoo"... "ces dénonciations ont trouvé un écho mondial inédit ". alors tant que l'égalité ne sera pas acquise mondialement, le combat continuera.

#florencerochefort #histoiremondialedesfeminismes #puf #presseuniversitairedefrance #quesaisje #feminisme #feministe #genre #droitsdesfemmes #liberte #egalite #essai #histoire #instabook #bookstagram #livre #book

text:
manifesting mondays -- time to uplevel! 
what have you been tolerating (in your life, love life, business, workplace) that no longer works for you? .

have you been tolerating…... poor performance from your team? being late or running behind in …… everything? not making enough money? stale love life? fickle friends? .

get clear on what’s not working. then, turn that energy towards identifying what you do want. hold the vibration of what you do want for 2 minutes every day. .

want a high performing team? imagine how it will feel to have this rockstar team. .

want to feel like a powerhouse? imagine how it will feel when you are running on all cylinders. .

want to make plenty of money to enjoy life fully and to share with others? imagine how it feels to be both responsible and generous with money simultaneously. .

want to have a deeply connected, passionate love life? imagine looking into the eyes of your beloved with passion throbbing through you. .

want to spend quality time with friends who love and adore you simply as you are? friends who are willing to have deep, raw, authentic conversations. imagine the joy of spending time with these friends. .

hold your imagination for 2 solid minutes without interruption every day for 30 days and see what happens. .
.
.
.
.
#womenleaders #women #uplevel #empoweredwomen #womeninbusiness #leadership #imagination #visualization #growthmindset #consciousleadership #metoo #awakenyourgreatness

text:
photo: the rape by picasso⠀
⠀
the first christian emperor constantine redefined rape as a public offense and ordered that if a woman had provided consent, she should be punished with her male abductor by being burnt alive. but even if she had not provided consent, she would be still convicted as an accomplice. the burden of proving lack of consent and innocence was put on the woman.⠀
⠀
read further on the history of rape culture and how women have always been suspect of some degree of acquiescence, and how rape trials have focused on the victims having to prove their innocence and lack of consent, more than determining the accountability of perpetrators  in the blog: “actresses in the history of rape culture”: https://buff.ly/2dkmdou⠀
⠀

text: *director’s note: “in coming down from the high of this weekend, i would be remiss in not acknowledging my guys, who have proven that we have truly entered the post-#metoo era. directing an all male cast was not nearly as intimidating as i was expecting, because they all showed up on set with nothing but dedication and professionalism. they trusted in my vision, deferred to my judgment, supported my ability to lead without ego or interference, and never made me feel inferior (even as a first time director) for being a woman, or gave the impression that they knew how to do my job better. i hope that every woman who has felt negativity or shame on set (or in any profession) can find the courage to keep going, and the opportunity to work with supportive men like @smallworld7 @frelawphoto @jordanlewismusic_ @hannasafar @thecharliewilde @callaird victor dante adriel gonzalez and the rest of this talented crew.” — writer/director of #thejustfilm @kandace.cornell

text:
uma tentativa do governo japonês que procura fazer com que os homens assumam responsabilidade na prevenção do assédio sexual no local de trabalho provocou um alvoroço on-line.
no pôster publicado pelo gabinete do japão, o ator japonês mikihisa azuma pergunta em japonês: “isto também é assédio sexual?” no fundo aparecem comentários: “você está mais bonita agora que emagreceu” e “roupa bonita hoje — esse é o meu tipo de visual”, com ilustrações de mulheres com cara de desaprovação. “você não é o único que decide o que é assédio sexual!”, afirma o cartaz.
os usuários que responderam a um tuíte publicado nesta semana para apresentar o cartaz da campanha disseram que ele adota uma visão muito complacente com os assediadores sexuais.
“percebi imediatamente que não havia mulheres envolvidas em nenhuma fase da criação”, dizia um comentário do twitter. “eles realmente não entendem (…) é por isso que não há mulheres políticas”, dizia outro comentário.
o gabinete afirmou que está a par das críticas e que as leva a sério, mas que não tem planos de alterar o cartaz.
“é verdade que decidimos direcionar isso para os autores de assédio sexual e aumentar a conscientização sobre a questão entre os homens, porque é um problema muito amplo e pode ser difícil para as vítimas se manifestarem”, disse takanobu hirowatari, do escritório de igualdade de gênero do gabinete, em entrevista por telefone.
o primeiro-ministro shinzo abe tem tentado atrair mais mulheres para o mercado de trabalho e para cargos de gerência como parte de um programa de “womenomics”, em um momento em que o país luta contra uma redução e um rápido envelhecimento da força de trabalho. o pôster faz parte de uma campanha anual de educação sobre a violência contra as mulheres, que neste ano será realizada de 12 a 25 de novembro.
neste ano, um grupo de ativistas lançou o #wetoo japan após decidir que era necessário proporcionar um amplo apoio às vítimas de assédio sexual e afirmou que a questão vai além da autoidentificação das vítimas do movimento #metoo, iniciado nos eua no ano passado.
fonte: exame 
#mulheres #assedio #japão #🇯🇵 #mikihisaazuma #governo

text:
"sitting on a muddy floor beneath a tarpaulin roof, nabila, a 19-year-old bangladeshi, fiddles with her shoelaces as she listens to tosmida, a rohingya woman in her mid-30s. both are crying. nabila, a student-turned-interpreter, says awkwardly: “she had it from all of them in her secret place.” this is the story of tosmida's rape, a story she finds hard to tell herself. @theeconomist helps us understand the complex emotional, linguistic, and cultural issues behind her struggle.

because when it comes to responding to crises like that of the rohingya refugees, language problems can be a barrier. and to address them, interpreters must grasp cultural differences as well as linguistic ones. #languagematters

text:
after doing more research on the cork rape trial i’m shocked and horrified to learn that this isn’t the first example of the victims underwear being held up in court. perhaps it was naive of me to think this. 
in fact, in 2002, there was a trial in scotland where a 15 year old boy was convicted of raping 17 year old lindsay armstrong. she was asked to hold her own underwear up in court despite the fact she was “hysterical”. her attacker was convicted, she later committed suicide. 
8 million women and 5 million men have been affected by sexual abuse or rape in the uk according to @safelineorg 
i’m appalled, disgusted and horrified by the rape case in cork. 
safeline has uk hotlines for men, women and young persons who have been affected by rape or sexual abuse. they will speak to you regardless of if the attack happened today or years ago. 
our bodies are ours to give and no ones to take. 💔 .
.
.
#thisisnotconsent #nomeansno #ibelieveher #ibelieveherireland #metoo #corktrial

text:
#internationalmensday 
so men.
i am with you,
just like you are with us. 
theres criminals that stand as shadows over your shoulder,
reminding you what society has grown to think of you.
but i do not see those shadows. 
i hear your #metoo’s,
i see you applaud for ours. 
i understand the fear to speak your truth,
because tears have grown into rarities for you.
but it is important to let them out. 
i am sorry society has failed you too. 
allowing your lives to go,
unnoticed. 
i am a women,
and i am sorry for the way women are putting you in a box. 
it is a box most men do not fit in,
but women are squeezing you in anyways,
forcing you to fit.
we ask our women to be believed,
but when is it the mens turn?
i am not talking about defending the rapist,
i am talking about believing the man,
who slits his wrists,
believing he should have enjoyed his torment. 
the men who are scared to talk about the gun, 
they have loaded in their bedside drawer.
the men who are put out on the streets,
because of their sexual orientation. 
the men who are raped by other men,
and instead of being supported,
are called gay.
the men who are scared to go to the doctors,
because being examined by another man,
brings back flashbacks from as young as 6. 
the men who are told their experience is less,
because of what is between their legs.

text:
“artreview” divulga sua aguardada lista “power 100” 
o galerista alemão david zwirner voltou ao topo da aguardada lista “power 100”, editada anualmente pela revista “artreview”. desde 2012, zwirner tem estado sempre entre os top 5: (2010; 4º), (2012, 5º), (2013, 2º), (2014, 2º), (2015, 3º), (2016, 4º), (2017, 5º). ele está na lista desde 2003. zwirner fois eguido pelo artista plástico norte-americano kerry james marshall (68º em 2017). este ano, pela primeira vez, a revista deu um posto a um movimento inteiro, o  #metoo, que ficou em 3º lugar. 
a artista hito steyerl, que pegou o mundo de surpresa ao aparecer no topo da lista no ano passado, caiu para o número 4. 
o chinês ai weiwei subiu da 13ª para a 5ª posição. os únicos brasileiros na lista são a galerista luisa strina (que caiu da 49ª posição para 79ª) e o trio de galeristas felipe dmab, pedro mendes e matthew wood (que cairam da 91ª posição para a 98ª). confira o artigo de kate brown para o portal internacional de artes artnet, editado em personalidade no site mapa das artes.

#davidzwirner #power100 #metoo #artreview #galerialuisastrina #mendeswooddm #lista #kerryjamesmarshall #sothebys  #personalidade #mapadasartes

text:
a different kind of before and after this gloomy morning. 
today marks 2 years since i was gang raped. 
scared and alone i took to food to intentionally and completely change my appearance, thinking being bigger would help keep me safe. but as i have learned, rape does not discriminate.
it has been 2 years since i lost my freedom, my happiness and my life. 
2 years of crippling anxiety, horrific nightmares and an emptiness no one could ever imagine. 
2 years of feeling dirty, worthless, disgusting, tattered, damaged and marked. 
waking up every morning, disappointed that i even woke at all. 
2 years resisting the temptation of suicide; as a way out, a solution and the only way i believe i will ever find solitude or peace out of what’s happened. 
because of this i’ve lost 2 years of my life that i will never get back. 
2 years that have turned into a blur, so much so i don’t even remember anymore what i used to be like before this ever happened. nor do i remember what’s occupied that space of time.
2 years of missed opportunities with friends, swimming and throughout all aspects of my life. 
2 years of paranoia that what happened once will happen again. 
2 years spent looking over my shoulder and constantly on edge. 
however like most things; time heals everything. physically you’re okay as all scars slowly fade. mentally it takes time, to heal and move past the pain. all while continually reminding yourself that it’s in the past. that you are no longer in that moment, that no one is hurting you and you are safe. everything is okay and will be okay. you’ve just got to take it one day at a time #metoo #metoomovement

text:
y'all know that i am the proudest nigerian🇳🇬❤, but can we talk??? nigerian academic professors requesting for sexual favors from students (predominantly females), in exchange for passing grades has been a known digusting and dehumanizing occurrence in the universities. i just stumbled on this article and interview by cnn and it filled my heart with hope for these young girls. they are finally finding their voices, and we need to support them!!! thank god for the #metoo movement, young girls are feeling empowered to share their horrible experiences. i am so happy and proud of this young lady that found the confidence to speak up. she also presented the recorded conversations with him. now her story and interview with cnn will change the lives of other young girls. 
sexual exploitation is still a huge challenge, not just in nigeria but around the world. we’re slowly winning the war that stomps on the well being of women. young girls should at least be able to obtain an education or pursue a career without being sexually exploited, or degraded. sexual harassment is one of the stressors that hinders academic work, and career performance.

let us be a voice to the voiceless! 
tip of day: girls, record the conversations (if you can) and hand it over to the authorities and the media. 
use your cell phone wisely to save yourself, not just to take slay photos! 🤔 ??who believes this professor deserves jail time- if found guilty. share your advice for the young girls!

full story: https://www-m.cnn.com/2018/11/19/africa/nigerian-university-professor-court-case/index.html

tip of day: girls, record the conversations (if you can) and hand it over to the authorities and the media. 
use your cell phone wisely to save yourself, not just to take slay photos! 🤔 ??who believes this professor deserves jail time- if found guilty. share your advice for the young girls!

today i am sharing a story with you that shook me emotionally and made me feel so much for a person who shared it with me. she did it for #thechoicevr project although i am not sure how much of the story you will be able to hear directly from her. what i want to share here is that for the first time for me it was not only abortion story, but also story about assault, overwhelming sadness, self doubt, and unwanted pregnancy on top of it. ⠀
i am writing here to ask you for advice. it was the first story like this shared with me and i very much hope i can help her with listening and just being for her, but she definitely needs help from people more experienced with the subject. so what i am asking is if you have some resources, know people or projects who work with rape survivors, please point me to them. so i can share it with her, and be prepared better for next time if needed. ⠀
thank you 💕⠀

text:
for those of you who have ever known me, have known that my depression, anxiety and self consciousness is awful. i've never really liked looking in a mirror, complimented myself, or gone longer than a few weeks without a breakdown- until lately. the past 2 months (since i left my abuser) have both broke me and fixed me. at first, i was all in the 'bye felicia' attitude. then i hit hard depression. didn't leave my bed for a whole week (literally). didn't leave my house much for another week. lost 2 awesome jobs for mental health. then one day i kind of woke up and realized i don't need anyone but myself. everyone else is just a bonus! so i picked myself back up and have been working on finding myself for once. i've always put myself on hold for relationships, or relied on the validation of others to help me through. but all of that was temporary. me. i'm permanent. my self validation is way better than what anyone could ever give me. so lately i've been saying 'no' to things that don't make me happy, and 'yes' to things that challenge me and push me to new limits! i've been applying myself mentally. going to group therapy almost every week- which has been amazing!!! and taking care of me, for once. i'm not even close to 100% yet, but i'm way farther ahead in 2 months, than i thought i would ever be. i've been dating again. i've been keeping up on my meds for 2 months straight. i've been trying to figure out an eating/sleep schedule that works for me- so far, no luck. i eat once a day and sleep when i am so exhausted that i pass out. i am starting new jobs coming up, to catch back up on my bills and get me out of the house again. i've been spending more time with friends i hardly see. getting closer to friends i never thought i would have. helping people after i've helped myself first. putting me before anything and anyone else. i have learned so much about life, thanks to my first love, who taught me communication and patience is so important. my abuser, who taught me to stand up for myself in any situation. and my bestfriends who have taught me love in an entirely different way.
thank you, to all of my past and current relation/friendships for helping shape me💋

into the life that can hold us
into the beloved that can hold us
into the unfolding of what could be

so- this week, the week of gratitude 
surrender into the life that is waiting for you
the connection that is waiting to unfold
the open heart that is waiting to embrace you

so much love ❤️

text:
おはよう。性暴力とかdvについて何か行動をしようとすると「ちゃんとしたフェミニストか？」に悩まされてない？とくに日本では。でも「週末ベジタリアン」もいるし「自分発信エコロジスト」もいる。私は、もっと楽に「フェミニスト」って言っていいと思う。安心して。

perhaps, if you try to do acting about sexual violence and dv, do you worry by the question "am i a right feminist?" especially in japan. but, "weekend vegetarian" and "self-styled ecologist" also exists. i think that you can be said easier. 
#metoo #remetoo #praisethebrave

building on the momentum of global movements and grassroots campaigns such as "#metoo", “#timesup”, “#balancetonporc”, “#niunamenos”, "#metooindia" and “hollaback!”, the un theme for this year’s 16 days of activism against gender-based violence (25 november – 10 december) under the unite to end violence against women campaign is "orange the world: #hearmetoo." #hearmetoo brings to the forefront the voices of women and girls who have survived violence, who are defending women’s rights every day, who are taking action — many of them very far away from the limelight or media headlines. their voices and stories must be heard, too.
#endviolence

text:
completely by chance, i came across this event and made it along last night. 
an amazing critically engaged talk with multiple mic-drop moments, particularly by kiruba and vqueeram talking about the lack of intersectionality in the movement in india and the class/caste/trans* erasure that has happened and still happens. 
a really insightful discussion which bears relevance to the global 'what next' of #metoo and mulled over ideas around the gap between the law and justice from a uniquely indian perspective.

@jenkshields i took so many notes. you would have loved it. and @khyeboi i could hear your clicking in agreement in my head the whole time.

text:
empathy... it's a huge reason i put up with as much as i did. it’s so easy to want to help, especially when you love someone.
.
i knew about his troubled past. i knew that everyone, all his life, had abandoned him. i felt his pain, because my past was painful too. and i believed, in my heart, that all he needed was to see one exception.
.
i wanted to be that “one exception” to introduce my abuser to a better world, one he could trust. but it never worked...
.
empathy needs objectivity. it can't exist the way it should when there's an imbalance of power or respect. no one's struggles can ever justify treating you poorly. and in an abusive relationship, the excuses and justifications will never end.
.
instead, we need to learn to step outside of our own emotional attachments, hopes, and goals, and see things for how they really are. because if we don't, we can lose ourselves in the process...
.
i know i'm not alone in this... talk to me below 👇🏼

text:
while i only took a few steps, i walked into the fresh snow today. this might seem like the most insignificant thing to document, but it was huge for me and an accomplishment worth talking about. those few steps were incredibly hard for me. i struggle enough with just walking around the apartment, or on cement or asphalt, which is why i use my wheelchair, and this was a lot more difficult. i struggled, a lot, but i did it. what you see here are the beautiful moments from those few small steps. what you don’t see is the severe tachycardia, the light headedness, the blood pressure drop, the full body tremors. for so many of us, these victories come with consequences and sometimes that tries to steal the joy that we felt, but i’ve leaned that it’s those moments of joy that carry us through the moments of pain. 💙

for me, the girl in the spider web is not about hacker, end of the world device, spy or government conspiracy
is about the story of two sisters in a broken family with a deranged and wicked father |

it's about sisterhood who lost their way, one choose the path of evil and the other is the avengers of wronged women
both trapped in the spider web , trying to get out, waiting just waiting for the spider to crushed them |

i don't care what the critics said, i loved the girl in the spider web |

text:
a rape trial in cork ireland - (#nytimes) during the closing argument, the defense lawyer asked the jury to consider the underwear worn by the 17-year-old woman at the time prosecutors said she was raped in a muddy alleyway by a 27-year-old man.
“does the evidence out-rule the possibility that she was attracted to the defendant and was open to meeting someone and being with someone?” the lawyer asked. “you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front.”
the man was acquitted.
#thisisnotconsent ———-
#corkrapetrial #corkireland #ireland #feminism #feminist #craftivism #craftivist #badasscrossstitch #embroidery #resist #persist #metoo

text: it's reassuring to know that we are drawn to another because of  our similarities or perhaps it's simply out of curiosity. when i look into your eyes, i'm curious to know what you see? what do i see? i see you! i see hope for a better tomorrow. a glimpse of silliness and at times a mixture of confusion and frustration that maybe life isn't going exactly how you planned it. breathe. does anything ever go exactly as planned? as a survivor of developmental trauma, the one thing you need is complete control. without it, life seems impossible. i consider myself a super organized freak. i laugh about it yet in reality i want to know what life would like look if i could fully trust and just be.

text:
backstage at the #obamasummit in chicago! as you might have seen on my story, i had the chance to meet president @barackobama today. i wanted to share what happened with him and the rest of the #communityleadershipcorps today because it completely reaffirmed my belief that he is forever my/our president.
.
this past august, i traveled with the @obamafoundation team to three cities, phoenix, columbia, and chicago, to speak to a total of 300+ young people who were chosen for their projects to better their communities. president obama surprised the whole group today to photobomb our group picture, and after saying a few words, he stood by the stage to shake hands with and give hugs to all three hundred participants.
.
he took the time to individually acknowledge every single person in the program, and later attended the smaller sessions to learn about some of their projects, all before taking the stage to speak to the whole summit about why he loves chicago, the importance of staying resilient and patient when it comes to community organizing, and his thoughts on power and human dynamics.
.
so much love for the @obamafoundation family and forever grateful for the opportunity to have been apart of the #communityleadershipcorps program. excited for what’s to come!

text:
i was called a “dumbass kid” for speaking up about being sexually assaulted. but that won’t stop me from telling my story. it won’t stop me from bringing awareness to a constant problem we have in society.
.
i share my story not for pity, but to help those who have gone through something similar feel less alone and know that they are strong and can get through the pain.
to shed light and help put an end to sexual abuse so that no one has to go through it.
.
i fight for my 11 year old sister.
my cousins.
my friends.
myself.
the people who are too afraid to speak up, because that was me. i stayed quiet for 4 years because of fear. but you cannot silence me anymore.
.
since opening up i have started to heal, and people have reached out to me and let me know that by sharing my story they feel like they can heal from their experiences.
.
this world is full of so much hate and darkness already. we need to spread peace, love and positivity.
.
stand up for what you believe in, even if you are afraid. don’t be silenced by others. you can truly make a difference in this world, let your voice be heard 🖤

text:
the universe has a funny way of letting us know we made the right decision, even years after the fact. when i decided to file for divorce going on 4 years ago now, i was full of emotions, to be honest, i was angry, i was hurt, i was exhausted. i had spent the better part of a year trying to get my then husband help for his addiction, however he didn't want help, he wasn't ready to admit he had a problem, and i was losing myself working four jobs trying to keep us afloat while doing all the cooking, cleaning, shopping, and other odds and ends. leaving was a hard decision, but in the end, after everything, i couldn't stay. a mutual contact reached out and let me know he's facing jail time for physical assault and dui charges. part of me is greatful that i got out, part of me is angry that he is hurting someone else, and part of me truly hopes still to this day that he gets the help he needs. i know i had to leave, staying wasn't an option, i had friends who didn't agree with my decision and chose to no longer be a part of my life. i never spoke about what was going on, just one day asked for help. i was embarrassed and scared. i'm sharing for two reasons. one, if you are in a similar situation and need to escape, reach out, make a plan, it's scary but you can start over. second, we never know if we are making the right choice in starting or ending a relationship, job, anything, but we have to take chances, and listen to your gut.. it's usually right.
.
.
.
#universe #reachout #divorced #relationships #escape #mychoice #listentoyourgut #harddecision #healthjourney #healthblog #wellness #mindovermatter #igotthis #positivevibes #motivation #determination #liveyourbestlife #livelaughlove #behappy #future #change #metoo

text:
＊
＊
＊
＊
フィンランド
＊
＊
イナリからロヴァニエミに移動中の
バスの中から撮影。
＊
＊
走行中にバスがいきなりストップ
＊
＊
何事かと思ったら
トナカイの群れが道路をふさいでいたり
＊
＊
何だか素敵でした。
＊
＊
日本では見たことがない
巨大なバスを
ガムをくちゃくちゃ噛みながら
女性が運転していたり
＊
＊
何だか素敵でした。
＊
＊
冬の日の出は遅く
日の入りは早く
夏は白夜
＊
＊
何だか素敵でした。
＊
＊
＊
＊
＊
＊
ムーミンの作者
トーベ・マリカ・ヤンソンはスナフキンを通してこんな言葉を言っています。
＊
＊
i do not believe only what i saw with my own eyes. 
but, what you see in this eye believe even that no matter how ridiculous.
＊
＊
僕は
自分の目で見たものしか
信じない。
＊
けど
この目で見たものは
どんなに馬鹿げたものでも
信じるよ。
＊
スナフキン(トーベ・マリカ・ヤンソン)
＊
＊
＊
モイモイ。
＊
＊

text:
"when you think all is forsaken, listen to me now (all is not forsaken), you need never feel broken again, sometimes darkness can show you the light". ~lyrics of the light by @disturbed ~
this song has been playing in my mind over and over this week as i shake the affects of ptsd and anxiety. these words ring so true! if you have never listened to this song i recommend looking it up. it really is inspirational when you feel like your mind is in darkness. ~
if you are struggling with depression, anxiety, ptsd, suicidal thoughts,  or any type of mental issue i beg you to reach out for help. there is no need to suffer. you are loved! 💜💜
~
~
~
~
#ptsdawareness #mentalhealthquotes #anxietywontwin #thereishelp #neveralone #enoughisenough #metoo #nevergiveup #thinksocialfall #handinhandbeauty

"when you think all is forsaken, listen to me now (all is not forsaken), you need never feel broken again, sometimes darkness can show you the light". ~lyrics of the light by @disturbed ~
this song has been playing in my mind over and over this week as i shake the affects of ptsd and anxiety. these words ring so true! if you have never listened to this song i recommend looking it up. it really is inspirational when you feel like your mind is in darkness. ~
if you are struggling with depression, anxiety, ptsd, suicidal thoughts,  or any type of mental issue i beg you to reach out for help. there is no need to suffer. you are loved! 💜💜

text:
its saturday 🌞
hello friends!!! .
.
ever felt as though you are the only one going through your circumstances or your storm and no one can relate to you or even understands how you feel??.. i've been there.
.
.
when you put up this pretty facade not only for social media but for the world as though everything in your world is perfect... when inside you are truly a crumbling mess!! ever been stagnant and so paralyzed mentally & emotionally by things that have happened to you that the thought of healing or moving on is simply a distant thought in the wind??...its ok!!! .
.
my book live through it..is a testament of that very same thought pattern... pretending to be someone i wasn't ... when in reality i was still this broken little 9 year old girl still acting outward on everyone else what i felt inward!! .
.
but through every mistake, every action, everything that has happened .... i made a decision to survive and live through it !!! and so can you!! 🌞
having been molested at the age of 9-10 by a family member, to dealing with a relationship that tried to take me out, battling stage 4 cancer with less than 6 months to live.... i knew i had to authentically write this book to encourage others to live through it
🌞
- by joining me on my journey through life you will find principles and applications that you can identity with and use in your own storms!!! .... we are more than conquers... we just have to live through it!!! .
make a decision today to no longer go through life operating in frustration, confusion, isolation and hurt!! head over to purchase your copy today 👇🏾👇🏾👇🏾
.
www.livethruit.com

text:
life with a narcissist will no doubt be an adventure. high highs and excitement is a guarantee! but there will be a whole lot of lows. lows that don’t get better over time. lows that won’t make the highs worth sticking around for the long haul.
.
narcissists have less than a handful of redeeming qualities, but buckets full of negative ones. negative qualities that are near impossible to remedy. negative qualities that shatter healthy lives. negative qualities that cause trauma, drama and chaos. negative qualities that can literally kill you.
.
try to focus less on the narcissist’s charm and all of the good times you had. focus on their true character. that’s what you’ll be stuck dealing with.
.
🤨 think i’m sounding a little disgruntled? think again. this list of adjectives are not only used by survivors, but mental health professionals describing individuals with this disorder. if this is how you would describe your narcissistic ex, you’re not bitter, you’re accurate. 💛🦋

text:
👆the woman who accused michael avenatti of domestic violence has now filed for a restraining order against the attorney.

according to court records obtained by the blast, actress mareli miniutti filed for a domestic violence restraining order against avenatti monday in los angeles.

miniutti is an actress in her 20s, originally from estonia, and most recently scored a cameo in “ocean’s eight.” as we reported, avenatti was arrested last week after a woman called police. he was arrested at his apartment in l.a. but the circumstances behind the allegations were unclear.

avenatti responded, “i look forward to a full clearing of my name and disclosure of all of the facts. i have never abused a woman or committed domestic violence against anyone. any claim to the contrary is completely bogus and fabricated. i am a target. and i will be exonerated.” #metoo

text:
• she feels the weight and responsibilities of her loved ones upon her chest, yet holds her head high. what is a queen without strength? what is a queen without endurance? 
with all this, she continues to be vulnerable. hurt her, if you will...she has already visited that room several times over.. she basks in sorrow without letting the dark things of life absorb her. she is a queen, not a commoner. she will hold herself high, she will hold her head high. 
you can charge towards her, but you will charge into a brick wall. 
only queens hold their strength; only queens hold their endurance. just like a brick wall. • deví •

.
.
.

“does the evidence out-rule the possibility that she was attracted to the defendant and was open to meeting someone and being with someone?” the lawyer asked. “you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front.”
the man was acquitted.

text: underwear or no underwear, this is not consent. lindsay armstrong is the second young girl to make national news for ending her life after her rapist’s trial, and quite frankly i am pissed. the 17 year old’s thong was admitted into evidence as a confirmation of consent in a sexual assault case. so defeated and humiliated, she felt suicide was her only option. women everywhere, everyday are being told they’re not in control of their own bodies, their sexual interests (or disinterest), our own clothing. we’re always “asking for it”, or “didn’t exactly say no”, or we “wanted it”. they make songs about our bodies and forget that we even have minds because we are supposed here to be “seen not heard”. we’re “dishwashers”, “sandwich makers”, “baby factories”. we don’t smile enough and simple niceties mean we’re flirting. it isn’t even about attractive women. it’s women in general. society deemed me unattractive a long time ago (check the tummy fluff), but i’m still afraid to walk alone in the dark, be in an elevator with a strange man, or even be kind to passerby’s at times because i’m afraid my body will be taken from me again. i’m so sick and fucking tired of misogynistic bullshit. i’m tired of “staying in my lane”, “playing my role as a female”. it’s 2018 and we’re still dealing with the same issues we had to when we burned our bras in the streets and marched for our right to vote and to be seen as people. fighting to be “equal” isn’t enough anymore. i want to be fucking respected. i want women to be safe, heard, and appreciated.  #istandwithlindsay #istandwithlindsey #ibelievesurvivors #endsexualviolence #metoo #metoomovement #imstandingup #thisisnotconsent #underwearornounderwear #underwearornot #rapeisntaboutwhatyouwear #rapeisntfunny #women #womenempowerment #womendeservebetter #womendeserverespect #istandwithsurvivors #shedidntconsent #ididntconsent #nomeansno #feminism #feminist #fedup #womensrights #womenarepeopletoo #iwontstanddown

text:
#خودت_باش_دختر
از باور کردن دروغ‌هایی که درباره‌تان گفته می‌شود دست بردارید تا تبدیل به همان کسی شوید که واقعا هستید. 
نوشتهٔ #ریچل_هالیس 
ترجمهٔ هدیه جامعی 
دخترها از سراسر دنیا از من می‌پرسن که چطور... چطور وقتی زمین می‌خورم دوباره بلند ‌شم؟ چطور توی زندگی‌م تغییر ایجاد ‌کنم؟ چطور با این ضربۀ روحی کنار بیام؟ چطور دوباره شروع کنم؟ چطور این بچه ها رو بزرگ کنم؟ سؤال‌هایی از این دست که از نظر من همه یک جواب دارند. 
بعضی از شماها حتماً از این یادداشت‌ها از من گرفتید... می‌گفتم که «تو یک مبارزی. خیلی قوی هستی. تو هر کاری که بخوای می‌تونی انجام بدی.» اما بعد از مدتی متوجه شدم اون جوابی که می‌خواستم رو نمی‌گفتم. اون‌وقت بود که سعی کردم کتابی بنویسم که جواب تمام سؤال‌های شما توش باشه، اگه دوست من بودید یا اگر خودم بودید؛ توی سن بیست، بیست‌وپنج، یا سی سالگی. 
و جواب اینه: تو قدرت تغییر زندگی‌ت رو داری. دیگه دنبال پاسخ سؤالاتت توی اینترنت نگرد. تو جواب رو می‌دونی. تو ابزارش رو داری. 
فکر کردم اگه این کتاب رو بنویسم و همۀ کشمکش‌های زندگی خودم رو توش بیارم، یا زمان‌هایی که نمی‌دونستم چه‌کار کنم و گیج بودم، وقت‌هایی که زمین خوردم، اشتباه ‌کردم؛ و اگه مسیری که خودم رفتم رو نشونتون بدم، اون‌وقت جرئتی بهتون می‌دم که توی مسیر خودتون هدفمند قدم بردارید. من نخواستم نظاره‌گر غرق شدن شما باشم. من توی محبت کردن آدم خشکی هستم، پس هرکس که مشکلش رو پیش من مطرح کنه باید پیه همه‌چیز رو به تنش مالیده باشه. می‌دونید، «من هم همین‌طور (#metoo)» از قدرتمندترین کلمات زبان انگلیسی هستند. و من از این تفکر یک بستر ساختم. و همچنین از این باور که «من اول شروع می‌کنم.» من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و راجع به افسردگی بعد از زایمانم حرف می‌زنم؛ راجع ‌به مصرف بیش از اندازۀ الکل، گرفتاری‌های ازدواجم، دشواری‌های بچه بزرگ‌کردنم، شرمساری از بدنم، سوءاستفاده و اهمال‌کاری و آسیب‌های دوران کودکی‌م. من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و اولین کسی می‌شم که بهتون می‌گه همۀ این اتفاق‌ها براش افتاده. و نه‌تنها این اتفاق‌ها رو تجربه کردم، بلکه تونستم با موفقیت ازشون گذر کنم. امیدوارم این کتاب جسارت انجام این کار رو به شما بده. امیدوارم وقتی داستان‌هام رو می‌شنوید و این کتاب رو می‌خونید بفهمید که تنها نیستید. پس به‌همین‌دلیل این کتاب رو نوشتم.

text:
#breakfast
aujourd'hui, j'ose enfin le dire haut et fort.
aujourd'hui, j'ose en parler à plus vaste que mes proches.
quand j'étais en troisième, après 10 ans d'amnésie, les souvenirs sont revenus.
c'est arrivé alors que ma grand - mère alcoolique devait me garder.
un homme avec qui elle buvait m'a violée.
le mot est fort, choquant. mais, s'il existe, ce n'est pas uniquement pour orner le dictionnaire.
•
aujourd'hui, je ne veux plus que cet homme et son souvenir continue de me détruire.
aujourd'hui, je ne suis plus une petite fille trop faible et appeurée pour pouvoir comprendre.
aujourd'hui, je décide de vivre la vie que je mérite.
aujourd'hui, je décide qu'il ne gagnera pas.
aujourd'hui, je décide que ce n'est pas à moi de me taire.
🍁
#fooddiary
compote pomme 🍏 ananas 🍍
🍞 tartine de pain aux graines, beurrées
🐓 tranches de poulet
🥜🌰 oléagineux
🍵 thé à la menthe et aux épices (toujours celui d'amsterdam ❤)
🍁

text:
owning my truth 🌞
*post contains some triggering content on ed and sexual assault*
•
i’ve been taking a bit of a break from posting this past week to focus on my mental health as well as to plan how i want to use this platform moving forward 🤔 i had a lot of plans and visions of how my year would look and you know what, sometimes life has different plans 🤷🏼‍♀️ 2018 has been a string of powerful lessons ✨ i wanted to share the top three hard truths that i have had to accept 🙏🏼
•
1️⃣ i was not deserving of sexual assault, nor was it my fault 🙅🏼‍♀️ i think in recent years, it’s become somewhat of hot topic, but the more people i talk with, the more people i realize that this is so much more common than we think. i was abused by a boy in my neighborhood starting at the age of 6 and this continued for a few years. it wasn’t until i was 23 years old that i even spoke about what happened with another human and then 25 (just this month) when i opened up to both my parents. in the beginning of this year, i dealt with another instance where i was taken advantage of sexually and it felt like pandora’s box had been opened yet again and i let it completely control my life. am i just some girl that allows herself to be put in these situations? i cannot begin to explain all of the negative and dark thoughts i had surrounding this experience, but i am taking my power back because i know that i am stronger than what has happened to me 🙌🏼 i believe we need to keep having open and honest conversations about sexual trauma, so more men and women feel comfortable to come forward and open up about their experiences- together we can help each other heal and break cycles of sexual abuse 💞
•
2️⃣ i cannot run away from my problems, they will always find me 🏃🏼‍♀️ over the years, i’ve tried just about everything under the sun to numb out the way i have felt from eating too much or too little, making myself throw up, drinking until i pass out, spending money i don’t have and putting myself in debt, avoiding responsibilities, sleeping too excess or not at all, and overall made some choices that have put myself in harms way 😰 (continued in the comments) ⬇️
name: Kaitlyn Kilcoyne

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian
